WEBVTT

00:02.166 --> 00:06.833
[♪ Bournemouth Symphony Chorus:
“Carmina Burana”]

00:26.083 --> 00:29.958
[music continues]

00:53.833 --> 00:55.000
[motorcycle revving]

00:55.125 --> 00:56.291
[woman screaming]

00:56.416 --> 00:57.625
[man screaming]

00:57.750 --> 00:59.625
[siren wailing]

00:59.750 --> 01:01.958
-Stop it!
-[man] Dude, how sick is this?

01:02.083 --> 01:03.000
[laughs]

01:03.125 --> 01:04.125
[loud thud]

01:04.250 --> 01:06.333
[boy 1] We're gonna die!
We're gonna die!

01:07.958 --> 01:09.333
[tires screeching]

01:09.458 --> 01:12.041
Oh, mama!

01:12.166 --> 01:15.583
[dramatic thud]

01:15.708 --> 01:18.208
[birds chirping]

01:18.333 --> 01:19.416
-[lacrosse ball thump]
-[kids screaming]

01:19.541 --> 01:22.291
[upbeat music]

01:22.416 --> 01:23.625
[player] Pass the ball!

01:25.375 --> 01:26.250
[upbeat music continues]

01:27.625 --> 01:28.791
All right, guys, bring it in.

01:28.916 --> 01:29.791
All right,
come on, come on, come on,

01:29.916 --> 01:31.125
Get in here. Huddle up.

01:31.250 --> 01:32.875
We got a minute left here, okay?
We are tied up.

01:33.000 --> 01:34.000
Lucas, whe--where are you?

01:34.125 --> 01:35.416
-Lucas, where are you?
-I'm right here, Dad.

01:35.541 --> 01:36.708
-Go, Lucas!
-Get in here.

01:36.833 --> 01:37.666
-You're on the team. Let's go.
-[audience] Come on.

01:37.791 --> 01:39.041
You're kidding.
He sucks.

01:39.166 --> 01:40.625
Nobody covered him
in the second quarter.

01:40.750 --> 01:42.333
I'm getting triple teamed
out there.

01:42.458 --> 01:44.375
Well, you know what?
Then I'll tell you what. Um--

01:44.500 --> 01:46.083
[kid 1] Dude,
have you even played lacrosse?

01:46.208 --> 01:47.416
[kid 2]
Just cold play, loser.

01:47.541 --> 01:49.416
Okay, fine. You know what--
that's a play.

01:49.541 --> 01:50.583
We're gonna get
the ball to Lucas.

01:50.708 --> 01:52.500
-[kid] What, are you high?
-Yes, that's the plan.

01:52.625 --> 01:53.541
Lucas, you're gonna take
the shot.

01:53.666 --> 01:54.666
We're gonna win
this thing, okay?

01:54.791 --> 01:55.875
Let's get in there.
What do you say?

01:56.000 --> 01:57.041
-[kid] I say we're gonna lose.
-I don't care.

01:57.166 --> 01:58.583
Let's win this thing
as a team, guys.

01:58.708 --> 01:59.875
-This is bullshit.
-Let's go, guys.

02:00.000 --> 02:01.458
Let's go.
We are heroes.

02:01.583 --> 02:03.083
Dad, are you sure about this?

02:03.208 --> 02:05.083
I mean, everyone's just gonna
be pissed off at me

02:05.208 --> 02:06.166
if I mess this up.

02:06.291 --> 02:07.416
Maybe I should just go
sit on the bench.

02:07.541 --> 02:09.125
Sit on the bench?

02:09.250 --> 02:11.208
Buddy, you are set up
for the hero moment.

02:11.333 --> 02:12.750
When we watch
those sports movies,

02:12.875 --> 02:15.208
and it comes down
to those final few seconds,

02:15.333 --> 02:17.250
and everything turns
to slow motion,

02:17.375 --> 02:19.291
that's where the hero emerges.

02:19.416 --> 02:21.208
-[slow motion] Whoa!
-[giggles]

02:21.333 --> 02:23.541
Everything slows down,
and they make the shot,

02:23.666 --> 02:24.958
and it's victory!

02:25.083 --> 02:26.250
And they throw 'em
on their shoulders,

02:26.375 --> 02:27.375
and they're going crazy.

02:27.500 --> 02:28.958
The girls are gonna be
“Lucas, Lucas!”

02:29.083 --> 02:30.041
-[chuckles]
-That's how we win.

02:30.166 --> 02:31.125
-All right.
-All right?

02:31.250 --> 02:32.166
-Let's do it.
-Let's make it happen.

02:33.708 --> 02:34.625
I love you, Dad.

02:34.750 --> 02:36.083
Okay, sshh.
Hey, maybe lower.

02:36.208 --> 02:37.083
This, this is sports.
We don't--

02:37.208 --> 02:39.333
we kind of--
it's already assumed.

02:39.458 --> 02:41.125
It's assumed.

02:41.250 --> 02:42.416
[whistle blows]

02:42.541 --> 02:43.833
Lucas!

02:43.958 --> 02:45.583
[upbeat, suspenseful music]

02:45.708 --> 02:47.041
All right, please, yes.

02:48.166 --> 02:49.208
Oh, please.

02:49.333 --> 02:51.250
Please, God.
Please.

02:52.416 --> 02:53.250
-[ball plops]
-Yes!

02:53.375 --> 02:54.208
[shrieks] Oh, my God!

02:54.333 --> 02:55.583
Lucas, go!

02:55.708 --> 02:57.583
-[excited screaming]
-[kid] Eye of the tiger!

02:59.166 --> 03:00.333
What the hell is he doing?

03:01.875 --> 03:03.625
Why is he moving
in slow motion?

03:03.750 --> 03:04.708
I might have told him to.

03:04.833 --> 03:05.666
[players screaming]

03:05.791 --> 03:07.208
[groans]

03:09.083 --> 03:11.416
No! He had no right!

03:11.541 --> 03:13.125
-No way!
-[kid] You suck, Lucas.

03:13.250 --> 03:14.708
[Brian] You're okay.
He's okay.

03:14.833 --> 03:16.291
You just got the wind
knocked out of ya.

03:16.416 --> 03:17.416
He got the wind
knocked out of him.

03:17.541 --> 03:19.083
He's fine.
Gonna come back quick.

03:19.208 --> 03:21.208
[weakly] Help me.
[coughs]

03:22.750 --> 03:25.041
Maybe lacrosse isn't his thing?

03:25.166 --> 03:27.541
I mean, maybe he's just not
a sports kind of kid at all.

03:27.666 --> 03:28.833
[ping sound]

03:28.958 --> 03:31.416
♪ Four leaf clover
won't you come over ♪

03:31.541 --> 03:34.458
♪ Baby, give me a chance ♪

03:34.583 --> 03:36.333
Look, playing a sport
is important to him.

03:36.458 --> 03:37.625
I mean, this is all I know.

03:37.750 --> 03:39.000
This is what I did.

03:39.125 --> 03:41.625
I--I connected with my father
through sports.

03:41.750 --> 03:45.041
Oh, honey, I know this whole
new stepdad thing can't be easy

03:45.166 --> 03:46.916
and I love that you're trying
so hard to connect with him.

03:47.041 --> 03:48.375
I really, I really am.

03:48.500 --> 03:49.958
You and Lucas will find
your thing too,

03:50.083 --> 03:51.875
but you just gotta give it time.

03:52.000 --> 03:53.583
You can't force it.

03:53.708 --> 03:55.208
Come here. I love you.

03:55.333 --> 03:56.166
I love you.

03:57.708 --> 03:59.458
Yo, Hunt. We'll get ‘em
next time, huh, bro?

03:59.583 --> 04:00.666
Don't call me “bro,” dude.

04:00.791 --> 04:01.750
Don't call me “dude,” son.

04:01.875 --> 04:02.833
Don't call me “son,” bitch.

04:02.958 --> 04:04.958
-I'm not a bitch, you're a--
-Oh my God, stop.

04:09.125 --> 04:10.125
You okay?

04:10.250 --> 04:11.833
Yeah, fine, it's just...

04:11.958 --> 04:13.500
By the way, how long does
it take Lucas to take a leak?

04:13.625 --> 04:14.541
Oh, can you check on him
for me?

04:14.666 --> 04:16.582
He gets bladder shy.

04:16.707 --> 04:18.000
Yeah.

04:18.125 --> 04:19.416
-[mean kids laughing]
-[door closes]

04:19.541 --> 04:21.041
Oh, shit.
It's Pukas.

04:21.166 --> 04:22.750
What's up, Pukas?

04:22.875 --> 04:25.582
[Lucas] Look, I'm sorry if I did
anything to piss you guys off.

04:25.707 --> 04:28.332
Honestly, I--I just want it
to be cool between us.

04:28.457 --> 04:29.582
[Kurt] Oh, shit.

04:29.707 --> 04:31.457
Hey! Don't touch him.

04:31.582 --> 04:32.625
[Kurt] Daddy's here.

04:33.957 --> 04:35.957
Let's go, Lucas.

04:36.082 --> 04:37.125
Let me tell you something.

04:37.250 --> 04:38.375
You touch him again,
I come back here,

04:38.500 --> 04:39.957
I personally kick
every one of your asses.

04:40.082 --> 04:41.207
Every one, every ass.

04:41.332 --> 04:42.666
I kick it, you understand?

04:42.791 --> 04:45.082
Just let's go, Lucas.
Come on.

04:45.207 --> 04:47.457
Do you understand what you guys
almost got into?

04:47.582 --> 04:49.250
Do you have any idea
the annihilation

04:49.375 --> 04:50.291
that would have
taken place here?

04:50.416 --> 04:51.500
Annihilation.
Wait, you want to go?

04:51.625 --> 04:52.957
You feeling frisky?
You want to go?

04:53.082 --> 04:54.750
You know what?
I'll go.

04:54.875 --> 04:55.791
-Hm?
-You want to go?

04:55.916 --> 04:56.832
-Let's go.
-How old are you?

04:56.957 --> 04:57.875
What the hell
where'd you come from?

04:58.000 --> 04:59.000
-Let's go.
-I don't--

04:59.125 --> 05:00.000
I'm not saying
I don't want to go.

05:00.125 --> 05:01.375
I'm just saying we can go.

05:01.500 --> 05:03.458
Stop talking shit
and just do it, old man.

05:03.583 --> 05:04.875
-Hit me.
-Bring the voice down.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.166
Okay, we're in a locker room.
It's a lot of acoustics.

05:06.291 --> 05:07.458
You just said you could kick
all our asses.

05:07.583 --> 05:08.833
I know.
I haven't even eaten yet.

05:08.958 --> 05:10.375
We have reservations
at Benihana.

05:10.500 --> 05:12.166
You know where they do
the smoking volcano thing

05:12.291 --> 05:13.250
with the runyons.

05:13.375 --> 05:15.041
It's fine.
Let's go, Lucas man.

05:15.166 --> 05:17.082
Go. Just...
better watch it next time.

05:17.207 --> 05:18.750
Yeah.

05:19.957 --> 05:20.916
All right.

05:21.041 --> 05:21.916
What's that kid's name anyway?

05:22.041 --> 05:23.332
-Kurt.
-Kurt.

05:23.457 --> 05:24.500
Freaking Kurt.

05:24.625 --> 05:26.166
Do you realize
how... how--how

05:26.291 --> 05:27.582
-that would have went down?
-Oh, yeah.

05:27.707 --> 05:28.541
I would have kicked
all their asses.

05:28.666 --> 05:30.041
-Yeah, definitely.
-Yeah.

05:30.166 --> 05:31.625
Now, I should go back there.
I'm gonna go back there.

05:31.750 --> 05:33.375
-No, no, no, no.
-He's probably not there, right?

05:33.500 --> 05:34.791
-I mean, I'm gonna--
-It's fine, Dad.

05:34.916 --> 05:36.250
I should just close
this shit out, man.

05:36.375 --> 05:37.625
-This is crazy.
-No, no, no, no.

05:37.750 --> 05:38.791
It's--it's fine, Dad.

05:38.916 --> 05:41.082
I'm used to it.

05:41.207 --> 05:42.250
What do you mean
you're used to it?

05:42.375 --> 05:43.666
That's not...

05:43.791 --> 05:45.332
see, that's not something
you should be used to.

05:45.457 --> 05:46.750
How often does this happen?

05:46.875 --> 05:49.041
Uh, every day.

05:51.375 --> 05:53.250
[Brian] I mean, there's no way
for him to escape.

05:53.375 --> 05:54.750
Did you know it was this bad?

05:54.875 --> 05:57.000
No. What should we do?

05:57.125 --> 05:58.582
Nothing now,
because I slammed it down.

05:58.707 --> 06:00.458
I shut it, you know?
I took care of things.

06:00.583 --> 06:02.125
I nipped it in
the bud, you know? So--

06:02.250 --> 06:04.166
You got to call the school
and the principal right away.

06:04.291 --> 06:05.333
What? No.
You can't do that.

06:05.458 --> 06:06.583
Then he's a rat.

06:06.708 --> 06:08.333
You saw The Departed.
He'll get whacked.

06:08.458 --> 06:12.000
Brian, you're his dad now.

06:12.125 --> 06:14.083
This is something a dad
needs to handle.

06:15.958 --> 06:16.791
You're right.
You're right.

06:16.916 --> 06:19.875
I...Hey, look at me.

06:20.000 --> 06:21.916
I promise you I'll never let
anything bad happen to him.

06:22.041 --> 06:23.666
All right?

06:23.791 --> 06:25.500
-All right.
-I gotta get back to work.

06:25.625 --> 06:27.791
When I get back, we'll take care
of this, all right?

06:27.916 --> 06:30.707
Hey, no more bullies.

06:30.832 --> 06:32.125
[man] Kick his ass!

06:32.250 --> 06:33.625
-Please get off!
-Oh, oh!

06:33.750 --> 06:35.000
Get him, you little bitch!

06:35.125 --> 06:36.707
[frat exec 2]
Dude, I got five grand on you!

06:36.832 --> 06:37.875
-[knock on door]
-[frat exec 2] Go, go!

06:38.000 --> 06:39.500
C--Claire said
you wanted to see me?

06:39.625 --> 06:40.916
Hey, buddy.

06:41.041 --> 06:42.332
Yeah, come on in.

06:42.457 --> 06:44.291
Just, uh, just grab--
grab a seat.

06:44.416 --> 06:45.375
-[frat exec 1] Go! Go!
-[frat exec 2] You can do it!

06:45.500 --> 06:46.457
Believe in yourself!

06:46.582 --> 06:49.125
[both] Yeah! Whoo!

06:49.250 --> 06:50.707
[frat exec 1]
Pay up, [indistinct].

06:50.832 --> 06:51.707
-[ball thwack]
-[groans]

06:51.832 --> 06:53.125
[boss] Hey, so listen.

06:53.250 --> 06:54.832
The Pfizer thing.

06:54.957 --> 06:56.416
You're gonna straighten out
those numbers, right?

06:56.541 --> 06:58.416
Well, I mean, the numbers
are what the numbers are.

06:58.541 --> 06:59.625
First of all,
don't yell at me.

06:59.750 --> 07:01.083
Okay, then.
I didn't think I was yelling.

07:01.208 --> 07:03.125
Sounded like yelling.

07:03.250 --> 07:04.541
Numbers are a little tight,
dawg,

07:04.666 --> 07:06.166
so just make them a little
loosey-goosey, you know?

07:06.291 --> 07:07.333
Well, I mean,
if we loosen them up--

07:07.458 --> 07:09.208
Hey, calm down.

07:09.333 --> 07:10.625
If we loosen them up,

07:10.750 --> 07:14.416
then what you're gonna do
is you're basically,

07:14.541 --> 07:15.833
you're asking me
to commit fraud.

07:15.958 --> 07:16.791
-What?!
-[all gasping]

07:16.916 --> 07:18.207
Whoa.

07:18.332 --> 07:21.125
Listen, Dad is gonna flip out
if he sees these numbers.

07:21.250 --> 07:22.582
Bro, you can't let Dad
flip out.

07:22.707 --> 07:24.332
You can't let Dad flip out.

07:24.457 --> 07:26.457
I mean, he's not--
he's not my dad.

07:26.582 --> 07:28.082
-What?!
-[female exec] How dare you!

07:28.207 --> 07:29.291
[frat exec 1]
You shut your face!

07:29.416 --> 07:30.416
Let me ask you something.

07:31.625 --> 07:32.957
How do you think
this is going?

07:33.082 --> 07:33.916
Well, I thought it was going
better when I first--

07:34.041 --> 07:35.957
That's not a question.

07:36.082 --> 07:37.832
But here's the answer:
[shouts] You're fired!

07:37.957 --> 07:39.457
-[glass shatters]
-My dad always hated you.

07:39.582 --> 07:40.750
-Okay.
-[dog barking]

07:40.875 --> 07:42.707
[♪ Ms. Money:
“Big Bootys Winning”]

07:42.832 --> 07:43.791
♪ Big booty bitches ♪

07:43.916 --> 07:45.041
♪ You're winning
you're winning ♪

07:45.166 --> 07:46.375
-♪ Drop it down low ♪
-[Brian clears throat]

07:46.500 --> 07:48.707
-♪ Yeah, spinnin' spinnin' ♪
- [Lucas grunts]

07:48.832 --> 07:50.457
[Lucas] Shake it, girl.

07:50.582 --> 07:51.875
♪ So you can't get
low, low, low ♪

07:52.000 --> 07:53.000
[moaning]

07:53.125 --> 07:54.500
♪ Big booty bitches ♪

07:54.625 --> 07:56.207
♪ You're winning
you're winning ♪

07:56.332 --> 07:59.541
So they called you
a baby back bitch?

07:59.666 --> 08:01.208
Do they do that a lot?

08:01.333 --> 08:03.166
No, it doesn't matter.
Whatever it is.

08:03.291 --> 08:05.500
I had to lay down the law
is what I did.

08:05.625 --> 08:06.666
But, you know,
there's the standards.

08:06.791 --> 08:08.458
There's standards.
I'm just cut from the cloth

08:08.583 --> 08:10.125
of a higher standard,
if that makes any sense.

08:10.250 --> 08:11.500
I don't know if it does,

08:11.625 --> 08:13.458
but that's--you--you get
what I'm saying, right?

08:13.583 --> 08:14.750
No, you're right.

08:14.875 --> 08:17.082
Yeah. You're right.

08:18.207 --> 08:19.291
What?

08:19.416 --> 08:21.416
You're such a badass.

08:21.541 --> 08:23.582
You're not a baby back bitch.

08:23.707 --> 08:25.041
We'll just have to cut back
on a few things

08:25.166 --> 08:28.707
until you find something else.
[sighs]

08:28.832 --> 08:30.750
Maybe we pump the brakes
on his dance lessons, huh?

08:30.875 --> 08:31.916
[Lucas grunts]

08:32.040 --> 08:33.250
Mm-hm. Mm, mm.

08:33.375 --> 08:35.290
We're paying for that?

08:35.415 --> 08:36.665
A lot.

08:36.790 --> 08:38.290
You know, I still have
that open invitation

08:38.415 --> 08:39.750
to rejoin my old firm.

08:39.875 --> 08:41.290
I thought you wanted
to stay home with Lucas.

08:41.415 --> 08:43.540
I do, but we also need
an income, right?

08:43.665 --> 08:45.500
So maybe you tag in

08:45.625 --> 08:47.333
and do the whole
stay-at-home dad thing

08:47.458 --> 08:49.000
for a bit.

08:49.125 --> 08:51.583
You want me to stay at home
with--with him all day,

08:51.708 --> 08:52.625
just me and him?

08:52.750 --> 08:53.833
It would just be temporary.

08:53.958 --> 08:55.500
Plus, it'd be so good
for you and Lucas.

08:55.625 --> 08:57.415
It would give you
all this one-on-one time

08:57.540 --> 08:59.790
to just like bond.

08:59.915 --> 09:01.333
♪ So you can't get
low no more ♪♪

09:01.458 --> 09:03.791
Ugh!
[panting]

09:03.875 --> 09:04.708
Was that good?

09:04.791 --> 09:05.625
[clapping]

09:05.791 --> 09:07.791
Very good, sweetie.
It was very good.

09:07.916 --> 09:09.541
There's really no way
to tell, pal.

09:09.666 --> 09:11.000
[bell rings]

09:11.125 --> 09:14.541
♪ I love vacation,
and I'm all numb--♪

09:15.875 --> 09:16.708
[chopsticks clank]

09:16.833 --> 09:18.166
Hey, bud.

09:18.291 --> 09:19.791
Aren't you, uh,
supposed to be in school?

09:19.916 --> 09:21.416
No, it's teacher
in service day.

09:21.541 --> 09:22.500
The hell is that?

09:22.625 --> 09:24.416
It's when teachers
learn new techniques

09:24.541 --> 09:25.750
to help them
with their teaching.

09:25.875 --> 09:26.958
And you get a day off for that?

09:27.083 --> 09:28.250
Why don't they work
that out on their,

09:28.375 --> 09:29.416
like, their own time?

09:29.541 --> 09:31.583
Well, I don't know,
but it's good for us.

09:31.708 --> 09:34.500
So what are we gonna do today?

09:34.625 --> 09:35.958
We?

09:36.083 --> 09:37.708
Boom. There you are.
A puzzle.

09:37.833 --> 09:38.875
Look at that.
Huh?

09:39.000 --> 09:41.208
It's 25,000 pieces.

09:41.333 --> 09:42.208
Yeah, it is.

09:42.333 --> 09:43.833
That's weeks' worth.

09:43.958 --> 09:45.625
Maybe even a month.
Who knows?

09:45.750 --> 09:48.165
-I'm kind of hungry, actually.
-Oh.

09:48.290 --> 09:49.165
Am I supposed to cook
you something,

09:49.290 --> 09:50.415
-or--
-Sure

09:50.540 --> 09:51.415
Is that what your mother
would do?

09:51.540 --> 09:52.833
-Mm-hmm.
-All right. Uh, yeah.

09:52.958 --> 09:54.750
Let's, uh, let's get after it.

09:54.875 --> 09:56.290
You ever try intermittent
fasting, by the way?

09:56.415 --> 09:58.165
-Intermittent fasting?
-Fasting, yeah.

09:58.290 --> 09:59.500
It's amazing for your colon.

09:59.625 --> 10:00.833
I'm in with you.
Let's both do it.

10:00.958 --> 10:01.875
What do you say?

10:02.000 --> 10:03.708
Okay, well... I'm sorry.

10:03.833 --> 10:04.666
I'm just really hungry.

10:04.791 --> 10:05.666
-Okay.
-Sorry.

10:05.791 --> 10:06.958
All right, uh...

10:07.083 --> 10:08.958
Sometimes Mom makes me
breakfast sandwiches

10:09.083 --> 10:10.541
with the King's Hawaiian rolls.

10:10.666 --> 10:11.750
Oh, these are cool.

10:11.875 --> 10:12.958
These are really good.
I like them.

10:13.083 --> 10:14.208
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

10:14.333 --> 10:15.291
All right, so you know
what to do with that,

10:15.416 --> 10:16.500
and that's--that's amazing.

10:16.625 --> 10:17.625
-That's really cool.
-Yeah, I think so.

10:17.750 --> 10:18.750
-All right.
-Great.

10:18.875 --> 10:19.958
-Yeah, yeah.
-Yeah, sure.

10:20.083 --> 10:20.916
You want to make them
with me or...?

10:21.041 --> 10:22.625
No, you're good.

10:22.750 --> 10:23.833
[distant chatter]

10:23.958 --> 10:24.958
All right.

10:25.083 --> 10:26.875
You wanna throw
the football around?

10:27.000 --> 10:27.875
Do a little boxing?

10:28.000 --> 10:28.875
-Nah.
-We could do, uh--

10:29.000 --> 10:30.416
How about this?

10:31.541 --> 10:33.540
[humming]

10:33.665 --> 10:34.875
Or just do weird crap
on your own,

10:35.000 --> 10:35.875
that's fine too.

10:36.000 --> 10:37.915
[alarm beeping]

10:38.040 --> 10:38.915
♪ What up, bitch? ♪

10:39.040 --> 10:40.375
[woman laughing]

10:40.500 --> 10:41.625
But you do owe me 50 bucks,

10:41.750 --> 10:43.040
I'm not fooling
around on that.

10:43.165 --> 10:44.000
[woman 2]
I'll give you 50 bucks.

10:44.125 --> 10:45.208
-Relax.
-[woman 1] You relax.

10:45.333 --> 10:46.958
I want my fucking money.

10:47.083 --> 10:49.040
This dude looks like
my AA sponsor.

10:49.165 --> 10:51.290
[woman] Dude looks like
my garbage man.

10:51.415 --> 10:54.375
♪ That gold crown ain't really
really relaxin' ♪

10:54.500 --> 10:57.083
♪ All twenty-six packs
on taxes ♪

11:00.875 --> 11:01.833
Who are you?

11:01.958 --> 11:03.208
I'm Brian.

11:03.333 --> 11:05.166
Do you party, Brian?

11:05.291 --> 11:06.416
Do I party?

11:06.541 --> 11:07.625
Mm-hmm.

11:07.750 --> 11:10.708
I mean, in college,
I did, I guess.

11:10.833 --> 11:11.750
I'm Leslie.

11:11.875 --> 11:13.291
This is Ivy, Jess and Marla.

11:13.416 --> 11:14.791
We got the Mama Mafia here.

11:14.916 --> 11:15.958
-What's up?
-What's up?

11:16.083 --> 11:19.291
Hello. Nice to meet you,
uh...Mama Mafia.

11:19.416 --> 11:21.666
Did you take my parking spot,
Brian?

11:21.791 --> 11:23.000
Oh, is that yours?

11:23.125 --> 11:24.625
All the gray Honda Odysseys?

11:24.750 --> 11:25.625
All of them,
are they all yours?

11:25.750 --> 11:27.333
-Yeah.
-Safest SUV on the market

11:27.458 --> 11:28.583
and gray's least likely
to get stolen.

11:28.708 --> 11:29.833
Is there a problem?

11:29.958 --> 11:31.125
No, no, no, I didn't know.

11:31.250 --> 11:32.875
And it was just felt
like crazy to me,

11:33.000 --> 11:34.665
but crazy sensible.

11:34.790 --> 11:36.915
Like you got the exact
same color and everything.

11:37.040 --> 11:38.500
It's pretty cool.

11:38.625 --> 11:41.790
-Snack bag?
-Oh, thank you very much.

11:41.915 --> 11:43.415
-I appreciate that.
-Those are for the kids.

11:43.540 --> 11:44.625
Yeah, I know they are.

11:44.750 --> 11:46.540
Give it back, Brian.

11:46.665 --> 11:48.665
Back, Brian.

11:48.790 --> 11:50.415
You've had enough
frickin' snacks.

11:50.540 --> 11:51.625
So you want to be in?

11:51.750 --> 11:53.040
You want to join the mafia?

11:53.165 --> 11:54.415
Do I want to join
the Mama Mafia?

11:54.540 --> 11:55.458
-Yeah.
-No.

11:55.583 --> 11:56.833
I don't--I don't even know,

11:56.958 --> 11:59.040
you know, what the Mama Mafia
really is about.

11:59.165 --> 12:00.791
It's easy. Weekdays,
we're here at 10 AM,

12:00.916 --> 12:02.125
we drop the kids,
they go apeshit.

12:02.250 --> 12:04.416
Yeah, at 12, we caravan
down to Chili's, eat lunch,

12:04.541 --> 12:05.833
and get ripped up.

12:05.958 --> 12:07.666
But mainly to get ripped up!

12:09.875 --> 12:11.208
Yeah, you want some wine?

12:11.333 --> 12:14.083
I...I don't drink so much
during the day, you know?

12:14.208 --> 12:16.583
You want coke?
Ivy's got speed.

12:16.708 --> 12:21.166
No, not now, 'cause I'm
watching my, uh, son. Um--

12:21.291 --> 12:22.625
You're gonna have to lose
the windbreaker, though.

12:22.750 --> 12:24.083
-Oh.
-You want to get jumped in?

12:24.208 --> 12:25.250
-Jumped in?
-Yeah.

12:25.375 --> 12:26.458
You can keep your clothes on.

12:26.583 --> 12:29.125
Uh, not right away.
You know what it is?

12:29.250 --> 12:30.625
Oh, that's Lucas.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.125
-Okay, that's my boy.
-[phone beeping]

12:32.250 --> 12:34.208
He's a wanderer
and my wife got him

12:34.333 --> 12:36.208
this wearable GPS tracker.

12:36.333 --> 12:38.540
-Did your wife pick your jacket?
-She might have.

12:38.665 --> 12:39.625
I'll see you later.

12:39.750 --> 12:40.915
-Uh--
-No, you won't, Brian.

12:41.040 --> 12:41.875
-[Brian] Okay .
- You freaking won't.

12:42.000 --> 12:43.875
[Brian] I hope not.
All right, Lucas,

12:44.000 --> 12:45.083
let's just try
to throw a spiral,

12:45.208 --> 12:46.125
-you know what I'm saying?
-Okay.

12:46.250 --> 12:47.833
Spiral.
You want to position your hand

12:47.958 --> 12:49.165
on the back quarter of the ball.

12:49.290 --> 12:50.500
Here you go.
It's just a nice, tight spiral.

12:50.625 --> 12:51.665
Nice and tight.

12:51.790 --> 12:53.333
Okay. All right.
Can you pick that one up?

12:53.458 --> 12:54.708
-[Lucas] Love you, Dad.
-Yeah, no worries.

12:54.833 --> 12:56.040
Try to catch those, okay?

12:56.165 --> 12:57.125
Makes it so much more fun.

12:57.250 --> 12:58.208
-[strains]
-That wasn't it.

12:58.333 --> 12:59.290
-I'm sorry.
-Okay.

12:59.415 --> 13:01.250
[Lucas] Sorry. My bad.

13:01.375 --> 13:03.000
This is gonna suck.

13:03.125 --> 13:04.041
Thread that needle, I see it.

13:04.166 --> 13:05.166
Was that good?

13:05.291 --> 13:06.541
That's more--
that wasn't threaded,

13:06.666 --> 13:07.708
that was more crochet.

13:07.833 --> 13:09.916
All right.

13:10.041 --> 13:11.666
[kid screams]

13:11.791 --> 13:12.708
[man strains]

13:14.375 --> 13:15.291
[kid strains]

13:16.958 --> 13:18.041
[man strains]

13:18.166 --> 13:20.541
[distant chatter]

13:20.666 --> 13:21.875
All right, Lucas,
let's turn it up a notch.

13:22.000 --> 13:23.000
What do you say, okay?

13:23.125 --> 13:24.000
-See what I'm doin'?
-[groans]

13:24.125 --> 13:25.583
Okay,
you try to catch those though.

13:25.708 --> 13:26.625
That's what you got to do.
You take it right in the chest.

13:26.750 --> 13:27.958
Hey, give you a little tip.

13:28.083 --> 13:30.000
It's these fingers
for a spiral.

13:30.125 --> 13:31.125
Yeah, I know
how to throw a spiral.

13:31.250 --> 13:32.458
It's probably
because you got tiny hands.

13:32.583 --> 13:33.875
It can be tricky
with little mitts like that.

13:34.000 --> 13:35.500
You just got to adjust
your grip like this.

13:35.625 --> 13:36.665
You don't, well--
I mean a little bit, yeah.

13:36.790 --> 13:37.750
Hey, what do you say
we play a game?

13:37.875 --> 13:38.875
Nah, I'm good.
I'm just...

13:39.000 --> 13:39.958
You thinking
like a little two-on-two?

13:40.083 --> 13:41.040
No, I'm not thinking
that at all.

13:41.165 --> 13:43.040
Okay, fun.
CJ, go cover his kid! Here.

13:43.165 --> 13:44.915
-I didn't even--
-Hike it. Hike the ball.

13:45.040 --> 13:45.958
I don't even know
what we're doing.

13:46.083 --> 13:47.415
Hey, stay tight on him.
Stay tight.

13:47.540 --> 13:48.500
[overlapping chatter]

13:48.625 --> 13:50.040
-That's all we're doing.
-Hike it, dude.

13:50.165 --> 13:51.250
[overlapping chatter]

13:51.375 --> 13:52.500
-I don't even know the rules.
-Ready? Ready?

13:52.625 --> 13:53.665
Can you just listen?
Oh my God!

13:53.790 --> 13:54.665
[ping sound]

13:54.790 --> 13:56.333
[screaming]

13:56.458 --> 13:59.125
[groaning]

13:59.250 --> 14:01.458
Oh look,
they're friends already.

14:01.583 --> 14:04.583
Shake it, girl,
come and get it.

14:04.708 --> 14:06.625
Do you mind, uh,
getting off me?

14:06.750 --> 14:11.083
[panting]

14:11.208 --> 14:13.208
Fatherhood, huh?

14:13.333 --> 14:14.375
Come on.

14:14.500 --> 14:15.750
Okay.

14:15.875 --> 14:16.833
[both strains]

14:16.958 --> 14:18.375
Okay.

14:18.500 --> 14:20.958
Oh, look, your kid's catching
a bug with my little bugger.

14:21.083 --> 14:22.958
Oh, that should keep them busy
for a while.

14:24.208 --> 14:25.333
I stand corrected.

14:25.458 --> 14:28.041
CJ, let it go!

14:28.166 --> 14:31.208
No! Drop it!

14:31.333 --> 14:33.208
[crunches]

14:33.333 --> 14:34.583
Hmm.

14:34.708 --> 14:36.500
Dude's always putting stuff
in his mouth.

14:36.625 --> 14:38.540
Your kid ever go
through that phase?

14:38.665 --> 14:40.375
Maybe when he was one.

14:40.500 --> 14:42.540
Yeah, we're taking
a little longer.

14:42.665 --> 14:44.333
Name's Jeff.

14:44.458 --> 14:46.040
Uh, Brian.

14:46.165 --> 14:48.375
Outstanding.

14:48.500 --> 14:49.583
You ever go by “Bri-Bri”?

14:49.708 --> 14:50.750
-No.
-Oh, come on.

14:50.875 --> 14:52.790
Bri-Bri is a badass name, dude.

14:52.915 --> 14:54.625
I knew a Bri-Bri
in the army once.

14:54.750 --> 14:56.583
Bri-Bri once used a severed arm
of a Taliban

14:56.708 --> 14:58.375
to diffuse an IED in a sewer.

14:58.500 --> 15:00.125
[chuckles]

15:00.250 --> 15:02.625
[sighs] I miss Bri-Bri.

15:02.750 --> 15:04.125
Was he killed in action?

15:04.250 --> 15:08.000
No, got crushed by a van
leaving Chipotle.

15:08.125 --> 15:09.791
What about one Bri?
Is that cool?

15:09.916 --> 15:13.041
-Sure.
-Okay, Bri...

15:13.166 --> 15:14.708
Bri.

15:14.833 --> 15:17.458
Okay. Uh, Lucas.
Let's get going, bud.

15:17.583 --> 15:18.708
-What do you say, you know?
-Already?

15:18.833 --> 15:20.541
-Yeah.
-We just got here.

15:20.666 --> 15:22.291
Yeah, I know but your mother
wanted us back

15:22.416 --> 15:23.375
for dinner and things.

15:23.500 --> 15:24.458
We got to get ready.

15:24.583 --> 15:26.541
-Dad, it's 10 in the morning.
-I...

15:26.666 --> 15:28.375
But CJ invited me
over his house.

15:28.500 --> 15:29.500
He just moved here

15:29.625 --> 15:31.125
and he said there's a tree
in his backyard

15:31.250 --> 15:33.165
that looks just
like Mark Ruffalo.

15:33.290 --> 15:34.790
Freakin' uncanny.

15:34.915 --> 15:35.958
It's why we rented the place.

15:36.083 --> 15:38.583
So can we go
over their house, please?

15:38.708 --> 15:39.625
CJ's cool.

15:39.750 --> 15:41.165
He said my hoodie's dope.

15:41.290 --> 15:42.665
It is a pretty dope ass hoodie.

15:42.790 --> 15:44.083
Please?

15:45.540 --> 15:47.250
[groans softly]

15:47.375 --> 15:48.625
Sure, sure.
All right. Why not.

15:48.750 --> 15:53.625
[dramatic rock music]

15:53.750 --> 15:55.083
-Hell yeah, dude!
-Yeah, okay.

15:55.208 --> 15:56.083
Fuck yeah!

15:56.208 --> 15:57.375
CJ, game on!

15:57.500 --> 15:58.415
They're coming
to our place, bro.

15:58.540 --> 15:59.875
Up high.

16:00.000 --> 16:01.125
-Whoa.
-Mm.

16:01.250 --> 16:02.708
Doesn't totally get high fives.

16:02.833 --> 16:04.416
[groans]

16:04.541 --> 16:06.041
You wanna dance?

16:06.166 --> 16:08.375
[both grunting]

16:09.458 --> 16:10.375
[grunts]

16:10.500 --> 16:12.083
I said submit!

16:12.208 --> 16:13.250
Submit!

16:13.375 --> 16:15.083
No, CJ! No!
Release.

16:15.208 --> 16:16.208
[grunts]

16:16.333 --> 16:18.041
CJ, stand down!

16:18.166 --> 16:19.166
CJ, stop it!

16:19.291 --> 16:22.500
[grunting]

16:24.583 --> 16:25.916
Little dude's super strong.

16:26.041 --> 16:27.375
Oh, yeah.

16:27.500 --> 16:29.250
You guys go on ahead
while I put him out real quick.

16:29.375 --> 16:30.500
-Okay, yeah.
-Okay, yeah.

16:30.625 --> 16:32.790
-Go to sleep. Sleep.
-We're gonna go.

16:32.915 --> 16:34.750
[pants, laughs awkwardly]

16:34.875 --> 16:36.000
I'm so excited to be here.

16:36.125 --> 16:38.583
Yeah, don't get too
comfortable, all right?

16:38.708 --> 16:41.250
I texted your mom our location,
you know, just in case.

16:41.375 --> 16:42.833
Well, just in case what?

16:42.958 --> 16:44.750
In case the guy murders us.

16:44.875 --> 16:46.000
-Hey!
-Hey.

16:46.125 --> 16:47.750
-Come in, come in.
-Hey, CJ. What's up?

16:47.875 --> 16:49.915
-[strains hard]
-[groans]

16:50.040 --> 16:51.040
-Okay.
-Don't let go.

16:51.165 --> 16:52.290
All right.

16:52.415 --> 16:53.583
-There we go.
-Yeah.

16:53.708 --> 16:55.083
Hey, I'm good.

16:55.208 --> 16:56.583
-Missed you, buddy.
-[weakly] Yeah, nice to see you.

16:56.708 --> 16:57.625
We're still unpacking,

16:57.750 --> 16:59.290
but I did clean the place
up for you.

16:59.415 --> 17:02.750
[clattering and clanking]

17:02.875 --> 17:03.750
[toy squeaks]

17:03.875 --> 17:05.500
Sorry. I'm beat, man.

17:05.625 --> 17:07.500
-Yeah.
-CJ barely sleeps.

17:07.625 --> 17:08.958
Lucky if he gets
two hours a night.

17:09.083 --> 17:10.500
Two hours?
That can't be healthy.

17:10.625 --> 17:11.625
Yeah, it's fine.

17:11.750 --> 17:13.415
What's that old saying?

17:13.540 --> 17:15.125
Kids are like horses?

17:16.833 --> 17:19.790
No, no one's ever
said that at all.

17:20.875 --> 17:22.583
Wow. Were you in the Army?

17:22.708 --> 17:24.250
I was.

17:24.375 --> 17:26.333
Well, that's Bri-Bri
with Commander Colonel Kurtz.

17:26.458 --> 17:28.708
First Special Forces
Operational Detachment.

17:28.833 --> 17:29.833
Delta Force.

17:29.958 --> 17:31.583
Whoa. Delta Force?

17:31.708 --> 17:33.041
Yeah. You know, one time,

17:33.166 --> 17:35.291
I saw two guys
get their heads blown off.

17:35.416 --> 17:37.583
[laughs]
One guy bled out in my arms

17:37.708 --> 17:40.208
while I slowly watched him die.

17:40.333 --> 17:42.208
Sick, right?

17:42.333 --> 17:43.875
-Right?
-Mm-hmm.

17:44.000 --> 17:45.083
-[whispers] Jesus.
-Wow.

17:45.208 --> 17:46.875
Pretty crazy story.

17:47.000 --> 17:48.375
I'm sure you got a lot more,
but if you tell me,

17:48.500 --> 17:50.208
you're gonna have
to kill me, right?

17:50.333 --> 17:51.291
-[tense music]
-I am gonna have to kill you.

17:51.416 --> 17:52.708
Hey, hey, hey!
Take it easy!

17:52.833 --> 17:53.708
-Hey!
-[gunfire]

17:53.833 --> 17:55.083
[ketchup splatters]

17:55.208 --> 17:56.541
Oh, shit.

17:56.666 --> 17:58.125
Oh, my God. I'm sorry.
There was some left in there.

17:58.250 --> 17:59.250
Oh, God.

17:59.375 --> 18:01.166
It's a ketchup dispenser.

18:01.291 --> 18:02.708
Came with a
matching mustard gun.

18:02.833 --> 18:04.083
Isn't that fun?

18:04.208 --> 18:06.583
Let me get you a paper towel.

18:06.708 --> 18:08.208
Hey, Dad. Dad.

18:08.333 --> 18:09.958
Isn't Jeff super cool
and strong,

18:10.083 --> 18:13.041
and look how big he is.

18:13.166 --> 18:16.291
Yeah, he's big, but it's--
it's genetics, you know?

18:16.416 --> 18:18.125
I mean,
I'm sure his dad was very big,

18:18.250 --> 18:21.500
and his mother
was an American bison.

18:21.625 --> 18:24.583
Plus, when you get that big,
you don't live that long.

18:24.708 --> 18:25.666
Okay, whatever.

18:25.791 --> 18:27.000
Uh, CJ, want to go outside

18:27.125 --> 18:28.416
so I can show you
some more dance moves?

18:28.541 --> 18:29.583
Hell yeah!

18:29.708 --> 18:31.916
-[both chuckle]
-[laughs]

18:32.041 --> 18:33.791
Oh, you're okay
with him cursing like that?

18:33.916 --> 18:35.666
Yeah, words can't hurt anyone.

18:35.791 --> 18:36.958
Worst case,
I tell him to go to bed,

18:37.083 --> 18:39.583
he calls me a buck-tooth bitch.
[laughs]

18:39.708 --> 18:40.666
[laughs awkwardly]

18:40.791 --> 18:42.166
All right.

18:42.291 --> 18:43.958
If you don't mind me asking,
I mean, where's CJ's mom?

18:44.083 --> 18:46.666
Oh, she passed away
a few months ago.

18:46.791 --> 18:48.333
-[mug thuds]
-Yeah, she was real sick.

18:48.458 --> 18:49.708
-[clanks]
-Sorry to hear about that.

18:49.833 --> 18:51.875
That's all right.
She was gonna die anyway.

18:52.000 --> 18:53.083
That's why we moved
to a new town.

18:53.208 --> 18:54.666
Make a fresh start, you know?

18:54.791 --> 18:56.666
Had some money saved up
from a security gig.

18:56.791 --> 18:57.875
Thought I'd do the
stay-at-home-dad thing

18:58.000 --> 19:00.250
while CJ gets acclimated.

19:00.375 --> 19:01.625
What about you?

19:01.750 --> 19:03.000
Your wife croak too?

19:03.125 --> 19:05.125
No.
She's alive and well at work.

19:05.250 --> 19:06.416
-Oh.
-Yeah.

19:06.541 --> 19:08.541
She's a lawyer.
I'm a forensic accountant.

19:08.666 --> 19:10.250
Oh, forensics?

19:10.375 --> 19:11.583
Like autopsies and stuff?

19:11.708 --> 19:13.666
Forensic accountant.

19:13.791 --> 19:15.875
Oh, that's boring.

19:16.000 --> 19:17.291
[CJ grunts]

19:18.708 --> 19:20.958
[bird caws]

19:21.083 --> 19:24.416
So what does CJ
stand for anyway?

19:24.541 --> 19:26.625
Christopher Jif.

19:26.750 --> 19:28.375
-Like the peanut butter?
-Uh-huh.

19:28.500 --> 19:31.166
Like this peanut butter?

19:31.291 --> 19:34.041
The one you looked at
right before you said Jif?

19:34.166 --> 19:35.375
Yeah, I looked
at the peanut butter

19:35.500 --> 19:37.416
because I was thinking
of making us

19:37.541 --> 19:38.875
some peanut butter sandwiches,

19:39.000 --> 19:40.958
which was CJ's
mom's favorite food,

19:41.083 --> 19:43.416
which is why
his middle name is Jif.

19:43.541 --> 19:45.083
[quirky music]

19:45.208 --> 19:47.458
Oh, hey, look at that fun list
of stuff I did for me and CJ

19:47.583 --> 19:49.708
to do now that his mom
went tits-up.

19:49.833 --> 19:52.000
-One, make new friends.
-Check.

19:52.125 --> 19:54.875
-Go to Buckee Cheese.
-Oh, love Buckee Cheese.

19:55.000 --> 19:58.041
Do ayahuasca in the desert.

19:58.166 --> 20:00.625
He's gonna love that.

20:00.750 --> 20:03.500
[speaking together] Freak out
the fat lady across the street.

20:03.625 --> 20:04.958
[laughs]

20:05.083 --> 20:06.125
[laughs awkwardly]

20:06.250 --> 20:08.208
Dad? Dad?

20:08.333 --> 20:10.250
There's a guy in the backyard
watching us.

20:10.375 --> 20:11.416
Where?

20:11.541 --> 20:12.625
Lucas is just kidding.

20:12.750 --> 20:14.083
No, I'm not.
I'm serious.

20:14.208 --> 20:15.458
There's a guy out there.

20:15.583 --> 20:17.291
-He's just staring at us.
-Come on, Lucas.

20:17.416 --> 20:18.500
Hey, I got an idea.

20:18.625 --> 20:19.708
Why don't we go get lunch?

20:19.833 --> 20:21.291
-You guys like Buckee Cheese?
-Sure.

20:21.416 --> 20:22.583
You can help us
cross it off the list.

20:22.708 --> 20:23.958
-Can we, Dad?
-Of course we can.

20:24.083 --> 20:26.250
Uh, you know,
he's got a dance lesson.

20:26.375 --> 20:27.666
[Lucas] No, I don't.

20:27.791 --> 20:30.166
Hope no one's allergic to fun.

20:30.291 --> 20:31.375
I know I'm not.

20:31.500 --> 20:33.083
Okay. Pile in, boys.

20:33.208 --> 20:34.583
What the hell is with
all the gray Odysseys?

20:34.708 --> 20:39.750
[suspenseful music]

20:42.458 --> 20:44.125
[upbeat music]

20:44.250 --> 20:46.250
[kids chattering, screaming]

20:46.375 --> 20:47.333
This is awesome, right?

20:47.458 --> 20:49.291
-[kid] You suck.
-[kid 2] Creeper.

20:51.166 --> 20:53.541
Man, that kid is fearless.

20:53.666 --> 20:56.083
Look at him hanging upside down
from--

20:56.208 --> 20:57.791
what's he hanging
upside down on?

20:57.916 --> 20:59.333
That would be
the sprinkler system.

20:59.458 --> 21:01.916
Oh. Well, you know
what they say.

21:02.041 --> 21:03.291
A kid falls
and cracks his skull,

21:03.416 --> 21:05.125
-that's how they learn, right?
-Mm, no.

21:05.250 --> 21:06.250
No, that's not how they--

21:06.375 --> 21:07.625
no one's ever said that.

21:07.750 --> 21:09.791
Look at how happy he is.

21:09.916 --> 21:11.125
You know,
this is the first time

21:11.250 --> 21:13.541
I've ever seen him smile.

21:13.666 --> 21:16.125
You never--you never seen
your kid smile?

21:16.250 --> 21:18.208
Since his mom died.

21:18.333 --> 21:19.666
Yeah, like,
I'm--I'm--I'm sorry.

21:19.791 --> 21:20.791
You know, I can't imagine
what you guys--

21:20.916 --> 21:23.083
Man, God is so good.

21:23.208 --> 21:25.416
You know, the first day my son
meets his new best friend,

21:25.541 --> 21:26.750
so did I.

21:26.875 --> 21:28.541
[kid] Fathead.

21:28.666 --> 21:30.541
-Do you want to start a band?
-No.

21:30.666 --> 21:33.333
Um, well, you know,
uh--Jeff, look, I--I--

21:33.458 --> 21:34.541
First of all,
this is--this is great.

21:34.666 --> 21:35.833
-I know.
-Yeah, and you...

21:35.958 --> 21:37.500
you just seem
like a great guy.

21:37.625 --> 21:39.166
-You do. You got the thing.
-[slurping]

21:39.291 --> 21:41.458
And--and things are moving kind
of fast with this whole thing.

21:41.583 --> 21:43.250
Like, a lot is going on
in my life right now

21:43.375 --> 21:45.541
and it feels like, you know,
you're asking a lot, you know?

21:45.666 --> 21:47.333
So first of all, I want
to tell you about myself.

21:47.458 --> 21:48.875
I've recently got married.

21:49.000 --> 21:50.708
-[foreboding music]
-[Brian's voice fades]

21:50.833 --> 21:53.208
It just feels like
I gotta concentrate on that.

21:53.333 --> 21:55.250
[foreboding music continues]

21:55.375 --> 21:58.166
[Brian's voice is not heard]

22:03.500 --> 22:05.166
[Brian's voice in normal volume]
You really can't be best friends

22:05.291 --> 22:07.541
with somebody
when things are moving so fast

22:07.666 --> 22:09.541
when you don't know
someone so well.

22:09.666 --> 22:11.583
I mean--Oh, no, no.

22:11.708 --> 22:13.458
Listen, I didn't mean--
I didn't mean it like that.

22:13.583 --> 22:18.458
[suspenseful music]

22:21.666 --> 22:22.958
Hello, miss.

22:23.083 --> 22:25.125
Can I get the super socks
for 500 tickets, please?

22:32.333 --> 22:33.791
Thanks.

22:35.458 --> 22:38.750
[suspenseful music continues]

22:39.958 --> 22:41.458
-[coins clank]
-[plastic thuds]

22:47.791 --> 22:49.541
-[coins clanking]
-[slow motion] Whoa.

22:49.666 --> 22:50.750
Holy shit!

22:50.875 --> 22:52.708
-Dude, what the hell?
-You broke his face!

22:52.833 --> 22:54.250
Sorry, I thought
he was a friend of mine.

22:54.375 --> 22:55.333
[♪ KC & The Sunshine Band:
“Boogie Shoes”]

22:55.458 --> 22:56.750
[teenage employee 2 groans]

22:56.875 --> 22:57.833
[upbeat music]

22:57.958 --> 22:59.333
Holy shit!

23:00.583 --> 23:01.458
[teenage employee 2 screams]

23:01.583 --> 23:02.666
No, no, no, no!
Aahhh!

23:03.875 --> 23:06.250
-[slurps]
-[children laughing]

23:06.375 --> 23:07.583
[exhales]

23:07.708 --> 23:09.458
[Buckee] Well, hello.

23:09.583 --> 23:11.375
Play with me, camper.

23:11.500 --> 23:13.125
[irritated groan] No.

23:13.250 --> 23:14.916
[teenage employee 2]
Oh, my God! [screams]

23:15.041 --> 23:16.583
[teenage employee 1]
Holy shit! Is this real?

23:17.916 --> 23:19.208
[teenage employee 2]
Somebody help us!

23:19.333 --> 23:20.250
-[Buckee giggles]
-Get your hands off me.

23:20.375 --> 23:21.291
Give me a hug!

23:21.416 --> 23:22.750
-No, no hug.
-Love me!

23:22.875 --> 23:23.875
Get the hell away from me,
you freaking weirdo.

23:24.000 --> 23:25.625
[groans in slow motion]

23:25.750 --> 23:27.583
[teenage employee 2]
Aahh! Please stop!

23:27.708 --> 23:28.625
[costume slits]

23:30.083 --> 23:31.583
[teenage employee 2]
Oh my God. Mommy!

23:33.500 --> 23:34.375
Hey, give me--hey!

23:34.500 --> 23:37.041
Ooh, shiny.

23:37.166 --> 23:38.250
Stupid!

23:38.375 --> 23:39.708
Who wants to be tickled?

23:39.833 --> 23:40.708
[Buckee groans]

23:40.833 --> 23:41.708
-That's enough.
-Dude.

23:41.833 --> 23:42.791
Just give me a hug, man.

23:42.916 --> 23:43.875
You just grabbed love handles.

23:44.000 --> 23:44.958
You don't do that.

23:45.083 --> 23:48.250
[grunting, straining]

23:48.375 --> 23:49.666
[teenage employee 3]
No, no, no!

23:50.875 --> 23:51.958
Don't be such a baby!

23:52.083 --> 23:53.208
Give me a hug, man!

23:53.333 --> 23:54.250
What's your problem?

23:54.375 --> 23:55.791
-Smile!
-Take the photo!

23:55.916 --> 23:57.333
-Smile!
-Take the photo, man!

23:57.458 --> 23:58.333
-[camera shutter clicking]
-Just relax!

23:58.458 --> 24:00.291
-I'm not paying for that.
-Yes, you are.

24:00.416 --> 24:01.333
-Thanks, Lucy!
-Stop it.

24:01.458 --> 24:03.458
Ow! Asshole!

24:03.583 --> 24:05.125
[Buckee blows raspberry]

24:05.250 --> 24:07.500
[quirky action music]

24:07.625 --> 24:09.708
Welcome to the jungle, bitch!

24:09.833 --> 24:11.708
[straining]

24:11.833 --> 24:14.916
[grunts]

24:15.041 --> 24:17.041
I'm gonna kick your ass!

24:23.166 --> 24:24.250
[kids gasp]

24:24.375 --> 24:25.625
[Jeff groans]

24:27.000 --> 24:28.041
How'd you find me?

24:30.833 --> 24:32.041
How'd you--?

24:32.166 --> 24:34.416
[whimsical music]

24:34.541 --> 24:36.166
[fast-forwarding sound]

24:36.291 --> 24:37.500
[man on speaker] All right,
shooters...

24:37.625 --> 24:39.083
[kids snicker]

24:39.208 --> 24:40.583
[man on speaker] ...hoedown.

24:40.708 --> 24:42.750
...moves, shoot it!
Let them critters have it!

24:42.875 --> 24:43.958
[indistinct]

24:44.083 --> 24:46.041
-[rapid firing of pellets]
-[grunting]

24:46.166 --> 24:47.625
Come on, big bitch!

24:47.750 --> 24:49.750
-Okay.
-Yippee ki-yay, mother--!

24:51.083 --> 24:52.333
-Hey, Dad!
-Hey, guys.

24:52.458 --> 24:53.708
Guess you missed
freakin' Buckee.

24:53.833 --> 24:55.000
What a freakin'--

24:55.125 --> 24:56.500
Hey, look at that, pizza's here.

24:56.625 --> 24:57.791
Thank you so much.

24:57.916 --> 24:59.583
All right, guys, dig in.

24:59.708 --> 25:00.750
What's that?

25:02.041 --> 25:03.333
What is what?

25:03.458 --> 25:05.291
Haven't you ever
had pizza before?

25:05.416 --> 25:06.791
No.

25:06.916 --> 25:07.916
[scoffs]

25:09.166 --> 25:11.125
Your--your dad's never
taken you for pizza?

25:11.250 --> 25:12.166
Jeff's not my dad.

25:12.291 --> 25:13.291
[ominous music]

25:13.416 --> 25:14.833
Jeff's not your dad?

25:14.958 --> 25:15.958
No.

25:17.208 --> 25:18.916
Who...who is he?

25:19.041 --> 25:20.166
I don't know.

25:20.291 --> 25:21.208
He just took me.

25:21.333 --> 25:23.166
[music intensifies]

25:23.291 --> 25:24.375
All right, that's it.
I knew something was wrong.

25:24.500 --> 25:25.708
Everybody get up, get up.
Get up right now.

25:25.833 --> 25:26.958
Come with me.

25:27.083 --> 25:28.708
Let's go.

25:28.833 --> 25:30.916
Look, ma'am,
this is an emergency, okay?

25:31.041 --> 25:32.000
His wristband
doesn't match yours.

25:32.125 --> 25:33.500
Okay, you're--you're okay
with a kid

25:33.625 --> 25:35.208
dangling from
a sprinkler system,

25:35.333 --> 25:36.458
but all of a sudden
an adult wants to leave

25:36.583 --> 25:37.875
with a kid that's not his,

25:38.000 --> 25:39.916
and you have a problem
with that?

25:40.041 --> 25:41.458
That didn't come out right,
but look--look,

25:41.583 --> 25:42.875
do I--do I look like a predator?

25:43.000 --> 25:43.958
Yeah.

25:44.083 --> 25:44.916
Is it the windbreaker?

25:45.041 --> 25:46.833
Yeah.

25:46.958 --> 25:47.833
No!

25:47.958 --> 25:49.166
Slow down!

25:50.500 --> 25:51.500
-[whispers] Sorry.
-Look, do you know this man?

25:51.625 --> 25:53.541
No. I don't know
any of these people.

25:53.666 --> 25:55.166
That's a lie.
That's a lie right there.

25:55.291 --> 25:56.750
You lie.
We met today at the park.

25:56.875 --> 25:57.708
-You don't remember meeting us--
-Buckee, thank you.

25:57.833 --> 25:58.958
-Please.
-What's up, pal?

25:59.083 --> 26:00.958
-Okay.
-You're a tough guy now?

26:01.083 --> 26:02.125
We've been through
this already.

26:03.875 --> 26:05.125
-[hostess] Buckee, look out!
-[Buckee] Oh, shit.

26:05.250 --> 26:07.541
[others scream]

26:07.666 --> 26:09.166
[hostess] Buckee! Holy shit!

26:09.291 --> 26:10.791
-Come here, man.
-[groans]

26:10.916 --> 26:12.000
[alarm blaring]

26:12.125 --> 26:12.958
You guys stay with me.
Stay with me.

26:13.083 --> 26:14.208
Hey, Lucas, stop.

26:14.333 --> 26:15.458
Hey, trust me,
you don't have a choice.

26:15.583 --> 26:17.833
Hop in, boys.
Seat belts.

26:17.958 --> 26:19.583
Hey, why did CJ tell us
you're not his dad?

26:19.708 --> 26:20.875
Because I'm not.

26:21.000 --> 26:22.708
Okay.
Lucas, get out of the van.

26:22.833 --> 26:24.416
I can't.

26:24.541 --> 26:26.083
I'm sick of this shit.

26:26.208 --> 26:27.750
Bring it, bitch.

26:27.875 --> 26:29.708
Who the hell are you?

26:29.833 --> 26:30.916
[dramatic strings]

26:31.041 --> 26:31.958
Who's that guy?

26:32.083 --> 26:33.250
A guy who wants to kill you.

26:33.375 --> 26:35.666
[cars revving]

26:35.791 --> 26:36.958
-Who are they?
-They want to kill you, too.

26:37.083 --> 26:38.250
-Why?
-Because they think you know.

26:38.375 --> 26:39.541
Know what?

26:39.666 --> 26:40.583
[Jeff] Get in, Bri!

26:40.708 --> 26:41.541
-[gunshot]
-[Buckee screams]

26:41.666 --> 26:42.666
[Buckee] Shit! Man!

26:42.791 --> 26:44.125
[gunshot, bullet ricochets]

26:44.250 --> 26:45.250
I don't know anything.

26:45.375 --> 26:46.708
Why would they think I know?

26:46.833 --> 26:48.416
[♪ The Spencer Davis Group:
“Gimme Some Lovin'”]

26:48.541 --> 26:51.166
♪ Twenty people knocking 'cos
they're wanting some more ♪

26:51.291 --> 26:53.625
♪ Let me in baby,
I don't know what you've got ♪

26:54.750 --> 26:56.083
[tires screeching]

26:57.291 --> 26:59.666
[tires screeching]

26:59.791 --> 27:01.458
-Dad, what's going on?
-Nothing.

27:01.583 --> 27:02.791
We're just having
a little fun.

27:02.916 --> 27:03.833
It's just some fun, right guys?

27:03.958 --> 27:04.916
-You guys having fun?
-Not really.

27:05.041 --> 27:06.708
Okay,
get those seat belts on now!

27:06.833 --> 27:08.333
[car honks]

27:09.458 --> 27:10.708
[tires screech]

27:10.833 --> 27:12.916
[car honks]

27:13.041 --> 27:14.166
[car honks]

27:15.375 --> 27:16.458
[Lucas] He's got a gun!

27:16.583 --> 27:17.916
No, no.
What the hell is that?

27:18.041 --> 27:19.583
[gunfire echoes]

27:19.708 --> 27:22.833
[tires screeching]

27:22.958 --> 27:24.125
[gunfire]

27:27.583 --> 27:28.416
[Brian] What are you doing?

27:28.541 --> 27:30.041
We're on a freeway.

27:31.375 --> 27:32.708
[tires screech]

27:32.833 --> 27:34.125
[gunfire]

27:34.250 --> 27:36.833
[tires screech]

27:36.958 --> 27:38.166
[gunfire]

27:39.416 --> 27:41.208
Just tell me
what the hell is going on.

27:41.333 --> 27:42.833
Hey buddies,
put some headphones on

27:42.958 --> 27:45.125
and throw in one
of my DVDs back there.

27:46.791 --> 27:48.291
[man on TV]
Doctor Hannibal Lecter.

27:48.416 --> 27:49.416
[soft, tense music]

27:50.541 --> 27:51.458
Can you just tell me?

27:51.583 --> 27:53.500
Look, they're not after me.

27:53.625 --> 27:54.750
They're after CJ.

27:54.875 --> 27:56.500
CJ? Why are they after him?

27:56.625 --> 27:58.291
Because I rescued him
from some very bad people.

27:58.416 --> 27:59.625
What--what kind of bad people?

27:59.750 --> 28:01.791
-I don't know, bad people.
-Okay, that's it.

28:01.916 --> 28:03.041
Do me a favor,
pull--pull over right now.

28:03.166 --> 28:04.708
-Let us out.
-Oh, no way.

28:04.833 --> 28:05.750
You've got one too.

28:05.875 --> 28:07.833
What the hell?
Are you kidding me?

28:07.958 --> 28:09.208
[Jeff]
Oh, your child abduction photo

28:09.333 --> 28:10.166
is way better than mine.

28:10.291 --> 28:11.250
Amber Bros.

28:11.375 --> 28:13.333
Okay, pull the car
over right now.

28:13.458 --> 28:14.708
I'm calling the cops.
That's it, you're done.

28:14.833 --> 28:16.500
Probably not a good idea

28:16.625 --> 28:17.958
with the whole Amber alert
and all, huh?

28:18.083 --> 28:19.000
The hell's my phone?

28:19.125 --> 28:20.458
Fuck!

28:20.583 --> 28:21.833
I left it at Buckee Cheese.

28:21.958 --> 28:23.625
I'm not turning around,
Bri-Bri.

28:23.750 --> 28:25.125
The hostess at Buckee Cheese
thought I was,

28:25.250 --> 28:27.125
you know, kidnapping the kids.

28:27.250 --> 28:28.208
Do I look like a child predator?

28:28.333 --> 28:29.375
It's the windbreaker.

28:29.500 --> 28:30.791
[car screen ringing]

28:30.916 --> 28:31.916
[in-car voice assistant]
Incoming call from Emily.

28:32.041 --> 28:33.750
Dad, why is Mom calling Jeff?

28:33.875 --> 28:36.625
Oh, uh, because I gave
Mom Jeff's contact info

28:36.750 --> 28:37.750
-in case--
-In case what?

28:37.875 --> 28:38.875
In case things
went really well,

28:39.000 --> 28:40.458
and then we became,
like, best friends.

28:40.583 --> 28:41.416
We're all just, like,
hanging out together.

28:41.541 --> 28:42.541
It's like, hey--

28:42.666 --> 28:43.625
Well, we don't want
to disappoint her.

28:43.750 --> 28:44.708
No, no, no, no.

28:44.833 --> 28:46.833
Emily!
Hey, how you doing sweetie?

28:46.958 --> 28:50.000
Oh, hi.
Um, is this Jeff?

28:50.125 --> 28:51.041
[Jeff] Hit me with it girl.

28:51.166 --> 28:52.083
I can't wait to meet you
in person.

28:52.208 --> 28:53.416
I've heard so many good things.

28:53.541 --> 28:55.208
-Okay, hey--
-Brian won't shut up about you.

28:55.333 --> 28:56.208
-Hey, Em.
-[Emily] Hey.

28:56.333 --> 28:57.541
Jeff sounds so nice.

28:57.666 --> 28:59.250
You said he was some kind
of like dumbass weirdo.

28:59.375 --> 29:00.541
[Brian] No, no, no, no.
He's not a weirdo.

29:00.666 --> 29:02.375
No, no, no.
I said he's like a speirdo.

29:02.500 --> 29:04.791
He carries a lot of spirit
and funness.

29:04.916 --> 29:06.041
[Emily] Oh, a speirdo?

29:06.166 --> 29:07.708
Well, look at you
making friends.

29:07.833 --> 29:09.208
Oh, wow.

29:09.333 --> 29:10.458
Are you guys in like
a high speed chase or something?

29:10.583 --> 29:11.625
Second one today.

29:11.750 --> 29:12.708
Crazy shit, right?

29:14.500 --> 29:15.583
It's insane indeed.

29:15.708 --> 29:17.375
Hey, how's that
conference going?

29:17.500 --> 29:18.625
[Emily] Pretty eventful,
actually.

29:18.750 --> 29:20.500
You'll never guess
who I ran into.

29:20.625 --> 29:21.916
That's awesome.
Say hi for me.

29:22.041 --> 29:24.166
[phone beeping]

29:24.291 --> 29:26.041
[tires screech]

29:26.166 --> 29:27.041
Buckle in, boys.

29:27.166 --> 29:28.208
What are you doing?

29:28.333 --> 29:29.458
Relax, Bri.

29:29.583 --> 29:32.041
Just let me do my thing.

29:32.166 --> 29:33.208
[♪ Corona: “The Rhythm
of The Night”]

29:33.333 --> 29:35.083
♪ This is the rhythm
of the night ♪

29:35.208 --> 29:36.625
♪ The night... ♪

29:36.750 --> 29:37.916
[tires screech]

29:38.041 --> 29:39.166
[car honks]

29:39.291 --> 29:41.583
♪ This is the rhythm
of the night ♪

29:45.166 --> 29:47.125
[strains]

29:47.250 --> 29:48.500
[Brian] Hey, hey.
Slow down.

29:48.625 --> 29:49.833
-[tires screech]
- You're gonna kill someone.

29:49.958 --> 29:50.833
[Lucas screaming]

29:50.958 --> 29:51.875
Hey, hey, hey!

29:52.000 --> 29:53.333
♪ Take me to the... ♪

29:53.458 --> 29:55.041
[screaming]

29:55.166 --> 29:56.333
What are you crazy?

29:56.458 --> 29:58.250
[laughs]

29:58.375 --> 29:59.375
[woman] Oh, my God.

29:59.500 --> 30:00.833
[panicked screaming]

30:02.958 --> 30:04.666
♪ Feel you give me love again ♪

30:04.791 --> 30:06.708
[tires screech]

30:06.833 --> 30:07.875
[screams]

30:08.000 --> 30:09.500
Whoa.

30:09.625 --> 30:12.958
♪ Round and round we go
each time I hear you say ♪

30:13.083 --> 30:14.416
-[tires screech]
-[kids groan]

30:14.541 --> 30:17.333
♪ This is the rhythm
of the night ♪

30:17.458 --> 30:20.125
♪ The night, oh yeah ♪

30:20.250 --> 30:21.541
-[whistle blows]
-[traffic officer] Hey, stop!

30:21.666 --> 30:23.083
-Stop!
-No, no, no.

30:23.208 --> 30:24.125
-Move.
-[Brian] No, no, no.

30:24.250 --> 30:25.333
-Move.
-[whistle blows]

30:25.458 --> 30:26.458
-Move.
-No!

30:26.583 --> 30:28.291
Move.

30:28.416 --> 30:29.708
[shouts] Read the signs!

30:29.833 --> 30:30.791
They're suggestions.

30:30.916 --> 30:32.541
♪ The rhythm of the night ♪

30:32.666 --> 30:34.708
[♪♪♪]

30:34.833 --> 30:37.500
[shouts] Hands on the wheel!
Hands on the wheel!

30:37.625 --> 30:39.500
-[car honks]
-[Brian] [shouts] Oh my God!

30:41.583 --> 30:42.916
[woman screams]

30:43.041 --> 30:44.250
[Jeff] Go, go, go!

30:44.375 --> 30:46.541
[Brian] [shouts]
No! Holy shit!

30:46.666 --> 30:48.125
[tires screech]

30:48.250 --> 30:49.458
-[shouts] Hey, there's a baby!
-[Lucas] Baby.

30:49.583 --> 30:51.000
There's a baby!

30:51.125 --> 30:52.500
-Run!
-[parents scream]

30:52.625 --> 30:53.625
[baby cries]

30:53.750 --> 30:55.291
Are you purposely trying
to hit people?

30:55.416 --> 30:57.291
-Uh-uh. Oh, shit.
-No!

30:57.416 --> 30:59.041
♪ This is the rhythm
of the night ♪

30:59.166 --> 31:00.125
[lemonade kid screaming]

31:00.250 --> 31:01.541
♪ The night ♪

31:01.666 --> 31:03.083
-[lemonade kid sobs]
-♪ Oh, yeah ♪

31:03.208 --> 31:04.416
Ha-ha.

31:04.541 --> 31:05.375
-♪ The rhythm of the night ♪
-It's you.

31:05.500 --> 31:06.958
-No!
-It's on you.

31:07.083 --> 31:09.083
Take the wheel.
All right.

31:09.208 --> 31:11.041
-Whoo!
-Keep going.

31:13.083 --> 31:13.916
[tires screech]

31:15.125 --> 31:17.750
[Brian] Look out! Oh, my God.

31:17.875 --> 31:18.708
[kid screams]

31:19.958 --> 31:23.083
[traffic noise]

31:23.208 --> 31:25.125
[man 2 on car screen]
We got a problem here?

31:25.250 --> 31:27.041
We got a problem here?

31:27.166 --> 31:29.041
We got a problem?

31:29.166 --> 31:31.541
[siren wailing]

31:31.666 --> 31:32.583
[Lucas] Oh, shit.

31:32.708 --> 31:33.875
[Lucas] Dad, the police.

31:34.000 --> 31:35.625
Oh my god!
Are you serious?

31:35.750 --> 31:37.000
Still want me to pull over?

31:37.125 --> 31:38.625
Remember, you're
a child abductor.

31:38.750 --> 31:39.958
You're a child abductor, Dad?

31:40.083 --> 31:41.166
-Put your headphones on.
-He is.

31:41.291 --> 31:44.250
[siren wailing]

31:44.375 --> 31:46.125
[Brian]
Man, what are we gonna do?

31:50.416 --> 31:53.041
Boom!
That was cool of them, right?

31:53.166 --> 31:58.166
[dramatic music]

31:58.291 --> 31:59.750
[cars revving]

31:59.875 --> 32:00.791
Look at this.

32:00.916 --> 32:02.041
It's like our tribe.

32:02.166 --> 32:03.708
The Mama Mafia.

32:03.833 --> 32:05.541
A bunch of drunk ass
soccer moms.

32:05.666 --> 32:06.708
Probably on their way
to have lunch.

32:06.833 --> 32:07.833
What kind of food?

32:07.958 --> 32:08.833
[♪ Knock Hard: “Uninvited”]

32:08.958 --> 32:10.375
♪ They wanna let me in ♪

32:10.500 --> 32:13.541
♪ but they're watching
my game ESPN ♪

32:13.666 --> 32:15.916
♪ studying the moves,
trying to replicate... ♪

32:16.041 --> 32:17.750
[car alarm buzzes]

32:17.875 --> 32:20.041
Oh, shit.

32:20.166 --> 32:22.375
A fricking pedo
drives one of ours.

32:23.750 --> 32:25.000
What--what are you doing?

32:25.125 --> 32:28.000
Blending in, Bri.
Watch this shit.

32:28.125 --> 32:30.000
[Brian]
Easy, easy. Whoa, whoa!

32:30.125 --> 32:31.375
[tires screeching]

32:31.500 --> 32:32.791
What the hell's she doing?

32:32.916 --> 32:34.375
-What the hell are you doing?
-Look, I can't be seen.

32:34.500 --> 32:36.000
You got an Amber alert on you,
bro.

32:36.125 --> 32:37.791
I think we're way past that.

32:37.916 --> 32:40.041
Ladies, our day
has finally come.

32:40.166 --> 32:42.250
Pedo on the parkway,
and he's right behind me.

32:42.375 --> 32:43.666
[Jessica] Oh my god, Leslie.
What do we do?

32:43.791 --> 32:45.291
Assume the diamond formation.

32:45.416 --> 32:46.916
This is what we train for,
ladies.

32:47.041 --> 32:48.041
[neck cracks]

32:48.166 --> 32:49.250
[Jessica]
Roger that. I'm going in.

32:49.375 --> 32:50.625
Watch my six, Marla.

32:50.750 --> 32:52.000
[Leslie]
Let's castrate this mother--

32:52.125 --> 32:53.625
Whoa. Whoa. Hey, hey.
Why are you slowing down?

32:53.750 --> 32:55.208
Cuz your girlfriends
are boxing me in.

32:55.333 --> 32:56.833
[tires screech]

32:56.958 --> 32:57.958
It's on, Bri.

32:58.083 --> 32:59.000
I'm gonna ram the shit
out of ‘em.

32:59.125 --> 33:00.375
Yeah, ram ‘em.

33:00.500 --> 33:01.750
No, do not ram them.

33:01.875 --> 33:04.833
[car revving]

33:04.958 --> 33:06.416
Oh, shit.

33:06.541 --> 33:08.000
-She's hot, bro.
-[Brian] Don't start with her.

33:08.125 --> 33:10.166
[car revs]

33:10.291 --> 33:11.708
Dude, she's a firecracker.

33:11.833 --> 33:13.333
I don't think
I can kill this one.

33:14.625 --> 33:15.625
What?

33:15.750 --> 33:16.583
[tires screech]

33:16.708 --> 33:18.041
Whoa. Shit.

33:18.166 --> 33:19.166
What up, bitch?

33:19.291 --> 33:20.416
Oh, I'm the bitch?

33:20.541 --> 33:21.583
I'm the bitch?!

33:21.708 --> 33:23.333
[tires screech, crashes]

33:23.458 --> 33:24.958
Can we not try
and kill her, please?

33:25.083 --> 33:28.166
[suspenseful music]

33:28.291 --> 33:29.166
[gun cocks]

33:30.458 --> 33:32.333
Eli! Eli,
take your earphones out.

33:32.458 --> 33:34.125
Get Mama's taser from her purse.

33:35.291 --> 33:37.416
No, not that one,
the other taser.

33:37.541 --> 33:40.500
Yeah, you're gonna put your
Fortnite skills to use, sweetie.

33:40.625 --> 33:42.333
See that dickface
in the front seat?

33:43.750 --> 33:44.708
No.

33:44.833 --> 33:45.833
That's man's a pervert.

33:45.958 --> 33:47.375
What do we do
to perverts, honey?

33:47.500 --> 33:49.375
We zap him in the ball sack.

33:49.500 --> 33:50.583
Face works too, honey.

33:50.708 --> 33:52.083
Make Mama proud.

33:52.208 --> 33:53.666
[taser whirrs]

33:53.791 --> 33:55.291
Little minion's trying
to execute me, dude.

33:55.416 --> 33:56.375
Just shut the window.

33:56.500 --> 33:58.041
I'm not backing down, Brian.

33:58.166 --> 33:59.458
-He's the enemy.
-He's 12!

33:59.583 --> 34:00.833
Exactly!

34:00.958 --> 34:02.500
Eli, what the hell
are you waiting for?

34:02.625 --> 34:03.583
Take him down!

34:04.833 --> 34:06.375
You ain't gonna do it.
You ain't shit, bro.

34:06.500 --> 34:08.125
You ain't shit!

34:08.250 --> 34:09.625
[car tires screech, thuds]

34:09.750 --> 34:10.708
[taser crackling]

34:10.833 --> 34:13.708
[screaming]

34:13.833 --> 34:14.958
Oh my god!

34:15.083 --> 34:16.583
Did you just see that?

34:16.708 --> 34:18.000
[tires screech]

34:18.125 --> 34:19.375
[grunting]

34:22.833 --> 34:23.750
[Lucas]
Dad, they're not stopping!

34:23.875 --> 34:25.000
What are we gonna do?

34:25.125 --> 34:26.416
Relax, Bri.

34:26.541 --> 34:28.250
These things have a way
of working themselves out.

34:28.375 --> 34:29.208
[truck honks]

34:29.333 --> 34:30.333
Ooh.

34:30.458 --> 34:31.958
You see what I'm saying, Bri?

34:32.083 --> 34:33.750
Woo! Yes!

34:33.875 --> 34:35.333
Oh my, pound it, dude!

34:35.458 --> 34:36.458
-Pound it!
-[Brian] No!

34:36.583 --> 34:37.583
I'm not pounding it!

34:37.708 --> 34:39.208
[Jeff laughs]

34:43.833 --> 34:45.208
-Whoo!
-Whoo!

34:45.333 --> 34:46.916
All right, that's it.
We're out of here.

34:47.041 --> 34:48.125
Totally.

34:48.250 --> 34:49.250
Let's take a breather, Bri-Bri.

34:49.375 --> 34:50.458
Stop calling me Bri-Bri, okay?

34:50.583 --> 34:51.458
We're not friends.

34:51.583 --> 34:52.958
Wow.

34:53.083 --> 34:54.791
What the hell is that?

34:54.916 --> 34:56.250
Thanks to your creepy
Amber alert,

34:56.375 --> 34:57.333
we got to steal another one.

34:57.458 --> 34:58.458
You stole that?

34:58.583 --> 35:00.708
You think I bought
some bitch-ass minivan?

35:00.833 --> 35:02.125
That's it.
CJ, Lucas, we are going.

35:02.250 --> 35:03.416
We're out of here.

35:03.541 --> 35:04.416
You're not taking CJ.

35:04.541 --> 35:05.791
Oh, I absolutely am.

35:05.916 --> 35:07.166
-Where are you gonna go?
-Home.

35:07.291 --> 35:08.250
Out of here.

35:08.375 --> 35:09.791
Away from this
freaking insanity.

35:09.916 --> 35:10.750
-[screaming]
-[tires screeching]

35:10.875 --> 35:11.750
-Yeah.
-[loud crash]

35:11.875 --> 35:12.791
[man] Oh, my God!

35:12.916 --> 35:14.416
Not a good idea, Bri-Bri.

35:16.375 --> 35:18.666
Really? Why not?

35:18.791 --> 35:20.375
‘Cause they're gonna find you
and your family

35:20.500 --> 35:22.583
and murder the shit out
of every last one of you.

35:22.708 --> 35:23.625
[faint rattle]

35:23.750 --> 35:24.708
What's your problem?

35:24.833 --> 35:27.166
Hey, Lucas,
stay in eyesight, huh?

35:27.291 --> 35:28.458
How are they gonna find me, huh?

35:28.583 --> 35:30.041
Cause they found me, Bri.

35:30.166 --> 35:31.625
And I drove 200 miles
to escape 'em.

35:31.750 --> 35:33.000
Ugh.

35:35.166 --> 35:36.250
Okay.

35:36.375 --> 35:37.833
[whimsical music]

35:41.708 --> 35:43.000
Wait.

35:43.125 --> 35:44.708
Okay, if I tell you the story,
you gotta promise

35:44.833 --> 35:46.458
-to keep an open mind.
-[sighs]

35:46.583 --> 35:48.166
You don't look like
you're gonna keep an open mind.

35:48.291 --> 35:50.291
I will keep an open mind.
Can you just go?

35:50.416 --> 35:53.083
So remember that security gig
I took when I left the army?

35:54.333 --> 35:56.666
Well, it was at this
top secret building.

35:56.791 --> 35:58.541
I didn't know who owned it
or what went on in there

35:58.666 --> 36:00.750
because I was never
allowed inside.

36:00.875 --> 36:02.291
The job was pretty strenuous.

36:02.416 --> 36:04.041
Lots of problem solving.

36:04.166 --> 36:06.458
And I got to pretend
I was Kung Fu freaking Panda,

36:06.583 --> 36:07.750
which was pretty
freaking awesome.

36:07.875 --> 36:08.791
Hiya!

36:08.916 --> 36:10.500
[clanks softly]

36:10.625 --> 36:12.708
So all I was told to do
was patrol the area

36:12.833 --> 36:15.000
and submit
to random drug tests, Ow.

36:15.125 --> 36:16.750
which I have no idea
how I passed,

36:16.875 --> 36:20.750
'cause there's like literally
no chance I passed.

36:20.875 --> 36:23.166
Anyway, so when I was working
this top secret building,

36:23.291 --> 36:24.583
the only other employee
I ever saw there

36:24.708 --> 36:25.666
was this bearded dude

36:25.791 --> 36:28.333
who looked just
like Zach Galifianakis.

36:28.458 --> 36:30.666
But it wasn't him, 'cause
I asked him once and he said,

36:30.791 --> 36:32.583
"No, but I get that
all the time."

36:32.708 --> 36:35.291
You see, we were never allowed
to give our real names.

36:35.416 --> 36:38.375
So I just called him
Galifianak-ish.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.166
So a few weeks ago,

36:40.291 --> 36:42.375
this truck pulls up to the
warehouse with a package,

36:42.500 --> 36:43.750
which was super weird

36:43.875 --> 36:45.416
because I don't even have
an Amazon account.

36:46.541 --> 36:48.208
[car hinges creak]

36:48.333 --> 36:49.875
I didn't want to leave it
outside all night

36:50.000 --> 36:51.166
in case it was something
super important,

36:51.291 --> 36:52.541
like the Ark of the Covenant.

36:52.666 --> 36:53.708
[owl hooting]

36:54.875 --> 36:56.125
[door alarm buzzes]

36:56.250 --> 36:57.416
So I brought it in.

36:59.666 --> 37:00.666
[laughs]
And that's when I heard it.

37:00.791 --> 37:02.750
-[loud thud]
-Oh, shit.

37:02.875 --> 37:04.916
You're surrounded, asshole!

37:05.041 --> 37:06.666
We're--we're all gonna
blow your head off.

37:06.791 --> 37:08.208
[answered knock on wall]

37:08.333 --> 37:09.708
Oh my god.
Who's there?

37:09.833 --> 37:11.458
[CJ] I'm in here.

37:11.583 --> 37:12.625
[Jeff] So I busted
through the door

37:12.750 --> 37:14.250
because I'm big
and freaking awesome.

37:14.375 --> 37:17.291
[gentle piano chords]

37:17.416 --> 37:18.833
And then what did I do?

37:18.958 --> 37:20.208
[♪ Harry Nilsson:
“Without You”]

37:20.333 --> 37:22.416
♪ I can't live... ♪

37:22.541 --> 37:25.000
I rescued him like a rescuer.

37:25.125 --> 37:26.500
Like the Yellowstone guy
from The Bodyguard ,

37:26.625 --> 37:29.541
but way more badass and cool.

37:29.666 --> 37:31.125
♪ I can't give... ♪

37:31.250 --> 37:33.583
And there you have it.

37:33.708 --> 37:35.208
-There you have it?
-Yeah.

37:35.333 --> 37:37.375
You are gorilla-ass crazy.

37:37.500 --> 37:38.833
Do you understand that?

37:38.958 --> 37:40.375
[♪ Scott Lee Miller: “Destroy”]
♪ Destroy ♪

37:40.500 --> 37:42.083
Agh!

37:42.208 --> 37:43.708
Liquid Psycho.

37:43.833 --> 37:45.666
This stuff's amazing, huh?

37:45.791 --> 37:48.458
[both gulping]

37:48.583 --> 37:51.000
A thousand milligrams
of caffeine.

37:51.125 --> 37:52.583
Is that a lot?

37:55.916 --> 37:57.625
I mean, I feel like I'm on fire.

37:57.750 --> 38:01.416
Like I'm riding a dragon,
like, like I'm white lightning!

38:01.541 --> 38:04.333
[rock music]

38:04.458 --> 38:06.500
[man] Kids! Kids!

38:06.625 --> 38:08.833
[passerby]
Oh my god! Calm down!

38:11.125 --> 38:12.750
[growling]

38:12.875 --> 38:14.916
[♪ Léo Delibes: “Flower Duet”]

38:15.041 --> 38:16.750
[upbeat music]

38:16.875 --> 38:18.125
[both screaming]

38:18.250 --> 38:22.916
[♪ Léo Delibes: “Flower Duet”]

38:23.041 --> 38:25.708
[upbeat music]

38:27.000 --> 38:28.791
[suspenseful music]

38:28.916 --> 38:30.625
[car tire screeches]

38:30.750 --> 38:33.500
[suspenseful music continues]

38:34.666 --> 38:38.333
[phone beeping]

38:38.458 --> 38:42.583
[tracker beeping]

38:46.833 --> 38:48.541
[cars revving]

38:51.208 --> 38:52.958
Now, who are these guys?

38:53.083 --> 38:55.041
Why don't we just go
to the cops?

38:55.166 --> 38:58.583
Well, there was
a little misunderstanding.

38:58.708 --> 39:00.000
What type
of misunderstanding?

39:00.125 --> 39:02.708
Good morning.
So here's the deal.

39:02.833 --> 39:05.041
He's not my kid, but
he's definitely someone's kid,

39:05.166 --> 39:06.041
so I had to steal him away.

39:06.166 --> 39:07.583
But now that I stole him,

39:07.708 --> 39:10.958
I think someone's coming
after us trying to kill us.

39:11.083 --> 39:12.416
You guys know
what I'm saying, right?

39:13.541 --> 39:14.541
[♪ Harry Nilsson:
“Without You”]

39:14.625 --> 39:17.666
♪ I can't live ♪

39:18.375 --> 39:21.708
-♪ if living is without you ♪
- [gunshot echoes]

39:21.833 --> 39:24.791
♪ Can't live ♪

39:26.000 --> 39:27.000
That is quite
a misunderstanding.

39:27.125 --> 39:28.583
Right?

39:28.708 --> 39:33.666
So cops are kind of out
of the question now.

39:33.791 --> 39:34.833
What?

39:34.958 --> 39:36.916
[distant chatter]

39:37.041 --> 39:41.916
[foreboding music]

39:47.500 --> 39:48.416
Is he coming?

39:48.541 --> 39:50.291
Check it. I stole these.

39:52.333 --> 39:53.666
No freakin' way.

39:53.791 --> 39:55.208
Pukas.

39:55.333 --> 39:56.958
What's up, Pukas?

39:57.083 --> 39:58.083
Is this your new girlfriend?

39:58.208 --> 39:59.375
[mean kid laughs]

39:59.500 --> 40:01.250
[distant car revving]

40:01.375 --> 40:02.750
We got a problem here?

40:02.875 --> 40:03.750
[♪ N.W.A.:
“Straight Outta Compton”]

40:03.875 --> 40:07.166
We got a problem here, punk ass?

40:08.416 --> 40:10.750
-[mean kids gasp]
-[mean kid] Oh, shit.

40:10.875 --> 40:11.791
You're frickin' dead.

40:11.916 --> 40:12.833
♪ Straight outta Compton ♪

40:12.958 --> 40:15.083
♪ crazy brotha named Ice Cube ♪

40:15.208 --> 40:17.041
♪ from the stupid-dope gang
wit a attitude ♪

40:17.166 --> 40:18.250
♪ So when I'm in
your neighborhood ♪

40:18.375 --> 40:19.458
♪ you better duck ♪

40:19.583 --> 40:21.750
♪ 'cause Ice Cube
is crazy as...♪

40:21.875 --> 40:24.291
♪ as I leave
believe I'm stompin' now ♪

40:26.041 --> 40:27.208
[mean kid grunts]

40:28.750 --> 40:30.750
-Yeah!
-♪ Compton ♪

40:30.875 --> 40:32.458
So nothing you've told me
is true.

40:32.583 --> 40:34.000
There's no dead wife.

40:34.125 --> 40:35.250
Well, that's good news, right?

40:35.375 --> 40:36.791
Okay.
So let me get this straight.

40:36.916 --> 40:39.208
There's a group of hardcore guys
out there that wanna kill me

40:39.333 --> 40:41.916
and my entire family,
all because you stole CJ

40:42.041 --> 40:43.208
from some secret facility.

40:43.333 --> 40:44.250
-Is that it?
-Yeah.

40:44.375 --> 40:46.208
Anything else you lied about?

40:46.333 --> 40:47.875
[awkward laugh]
Actually, I might have lied

40:48.000 --> 40:48.875
about something else.

40:49.000 --> 40:50.125
Yeah, I'm feeling that.

40:50.250 --> 40:53.541
CJ's name
isn't Christopher Jif.

40:53.666 --> 40:54.791
It's not?

40:54.916 --> 40:55.875
That's a peanut butter.

40:56.000 --> 40:57.375
I don't know
what it stands for.

40:57.500 --> 40:59.750
So, you're right, Bri.

40:59.875 --> 41:01.625
All we have is each other now.

41:01.750 --> 41:03.041
I never said that.

41:03.166 --> 41:04.791
Lucas, CJ, let's go.

41:04.958 --> 41:05.833
Where the hell are they?

41:05.958 --> 41:07.625
Lucas! CJ!

41:07.750 --> 41:08.958
CJ!

41:09.083 --> 41:10.416
-[car revving]
-[tires screech]

41:10.541 --> 41:11.500
-[woman screams]
-[Brian] Oh, my God!

41:11.625 --> 41:12.583
They found us.

41:14.708 --> 41:15.625
[car revving]

41:15.750 --> 41:16.583
[Brian] What are you doing?

41:16.708 --> 41:17.583
Stealing a car.

41:17.708 --> 41:20.875
Eenie-meenie-miney-mo.

41:21.000 --> 41:23.333
Now is this meant to be
or is this meant to be?

41:23.458 --> 41:25.041
-I'm gonna get my kid.
-Bri-Bri!

41:26.125 --> 41:27.291
Damn it.

41:30.833 --> 41:33.166
[phone beeping]

41:38.208 --> 41:41.125
[faint music]

41:41.250 --> 41:42.708
-[suspenseful music]
-Lucas!

41:48.500 --> 41:49.833
Lucas!

41:49.958 --> 41:51.750
-[woman] What's happening?
-Lucas!

41:51.875 --> 41:53.625
[woman] She brought a casserole.
It was awful.

41:57.000 --> 42:01.875
[foreboding music]

42:05.500 --> 42:06.875
[car revs]

42:07.000 --> 42:08.375
-Lucas!
-[woman] What's going on?

42:09.708 --> 42:11.166
Lucas!

42:11.291 --> 42:12.916
[gunshot]

42:13.041 --> 42:14.291
[woman] Oh, my God!

42:18.333 --> 42:20.541
[panicked screaming]

42:20.666 --> 42:22.041
Lucas!

42:22.166 --> 42:26.541
[suspenseful music]

42:26.666 --> 42:28.000
Lucas!

42:31.583 --> 42:32.583
[gasps]

42:32.708 --> 42:34.250
It's okay. It's okay.

42:34.375 --> 42:35.875
I got you, all right?

42:36.000 --> 42:40.125
-You're safe, you're safe.
-No, no. Where's Jeff?

42:40.250 --> 42:41.375
We don't need Jeff, okay?

42:41.500 --> 42:43.583
No, we gotta find Jeff.

42:43.708 --> 42:45.916
He needs to protect us, Dad.

42:46.041 --> 42:47.500
We gotta find him.

42:49.958 --> 42:51.208
No, no, no!

42:51.333 --> 42:52.541
[Lucas] No!

42:52.666 --> 42:53.666
No! No, no, no! No!

42:53.791 --> 42:56.000
-[gunman grunts]
-[tires screech]

42:56.125 --> 42:57.208
You see that?

42:57.333 --> 42:58.583
Sick, right?

42:58.708 --> 43:00.250
[laughs] God, I'm good!

43:00.375 --> 43:01.750
Okay, not bad.

43:01.875 --> 43:03.250
[tires screech]

43:04.875 --> 43:07.625
[dramatic music]

43:07.750 --> 43:08.875
Dad, they're still coming.

43:09.000 --> 43:10.750
Go, go, go, go!

43:12.833 --> 43:13.708
Are they coming?

43:13.833 --> 43:15.083
[music trails off]

43:16.416 --> 43:17.791
How do they keep finding us?

43:17.916 --> 43:19.625
You thinking Treadstone?

43:19.750 --> 43:21.166
Okay, that's a movie.
That's not real.

43:21.291 --> 43:22.541
You know,
the way they track Matt Damon.

43:22.666 --> 43:24.666
You know, everything on us
is traceable.

43:24.791 --> 43:26.708
That's it.
They have my phone.

43:26.833 --> 43:28.625
They're--they're tracking Lucas
with my phone.

43:28.750 --> 43:30.083
Okay, Lucas,
take your GPS button

43:30.208 --> 43:31.208
and turn it off, okay?

43:31.333 --> 43:32.208
And keep it off.

43:32.333 --> 43:33.375
[GPS tracker beeps]

43:33.500 --> 43:34.458
Yeah, keep it off, Lucas.

43:34.583 --> 43:36.375
This is all your fault.

43:36.500 --> 43:37.375
I'm kidding, dude.

43:37.500 --> 43:38.791
I'm kidding.

43:38.916 --> 43:41.291
It's mostly your fault,
but not all your fault.

43:41.416 --> 43:42.833
Thanks for what you did
back there.

43:44.041 --> 43:46.000
That was really cool of you.

43:46.125 --> 43:47.000
Cool.

43:47.125 --> 43:48.166
[chuckles]

43:50.666 --> 43:52.916
-[groans]
-Ow.

43:53.041 --> 43:55.416
[car revving]

43:55.541 --> 43:58.375
[Brian] Huh, this is crazy.

43:58.500 --> 44:00.375
I don't even know
what I'm thinking, man.

44:00.500 --> 44:02.458
-What?
-Can't even be a good dad.

44:02.583 --> 44:04.000
What are you talking about?

44:04.125 --> 44:06.416
You're the one
who saved him, Bri.

44:06.541 --> 44:08.416
You're a great dad.

44:08.541 --> 44:11.125
And you got a great kid.

44:11.250 --> 44:12.375
Kid who loves you.

44:13.833 --> 44:15.041
I don't know about that.

44:17.041 --> 44:21.208
You know...I gotta tell you
being a stepdad is...

44:21.333 --> 44:24.875
I thought I'd have kids
in my 20s or 30s.

44:25.000 --> 44:25.958
That didn't happen.

44:26.083 --> 44:27.541
I was okay with that.

44:27.666 --> 44:29.916
But then they put Emily
in my life

44:30.041 --> 44:32.583
and I was like, wow, you know,
this amazing woman

44:32.708 --> 44:35.833
who's kind of
out of my league.

44:35.958 --> 44:38.541
Totally out of your league.
Like way, way out.

44:38.666 --> 44:39.916
-Okay.
-Like looks.

44:40.041 --> 44:41.958
-Yeah, that.
-Personality.

44:42.083 --> 44:43.333
Pretty much every way possible.

44:43.458 --> 44:45.791
I got it.
I got what you're saying.

44:45.916 --> 44:47.500
And she came with this kid...

44:50.208 --> 44:52.416
[gentle music]

44:52.541 --> 44:58.458
and he started calling me Dad
and I was like, “Oh, man.”

44:58.583 --> 45:01.541
You know, I don't know how
to do this stuff, you know?

45:01.666 --> 45:05.375
And I thought I didn't even
deserve to be called Dad.

45:05.500 --> 45:09.166
I started feeling bad
for him, you know?

45:09.291 --> 45:11.666
He got saddled with
an old guy like me.

45:11.791 --> 45:14.125
What are you,
a cool guy like you?

45:14.250 --> 45:16.375
Bri, you're a great guy.

45:16.500 --> 45:20.416
Like, I'd kill
to have a dad like you.

45:20.541 --> 45:22.958
And the way you take care
of him is so cool.

45:23.083 --> 45:27.958
[soft, uneasy music]

45:30.666 --> 45:33.208
We gotta get
them some place safe, okay?

45:33.333 --> 45:35.666
Some place completely
off the grid.

45:37.166 --> 45:40.083
I know just the place.

45:40.208 --> 45:42.416
They'll never find us.

45:42.541 --> 45:47.625
[mellow music]

45:47.750 --> 45:49.583
This is where we're hiding out?

45:49.708 --> 45:50.958
Sick, right?

45:52.125 --> 45:53.583
-[old man gasps]
-[woman screams]

45:53.708 --> 45:54.583
[car door closes]

45:56.125 --> 45:56.958
[door knocking]

45:57.583 --> 45:59.833
-Look at you.
-[woman] Gordon, I'm naked!

46:01.000 --> 46:02.208
-Jeff?
-Hey, Gordon.

46:02.333 --> 46:03.375
Hey.

46:03.500 --> 46:04.500
Brian, this is Gordon,

46:04.625 --> 46:06.916
-my estranged deadbeat dad.
-Pleasure.

46:07.041 --> 46:09.375
That's Lucas, Brian's son,
and this here is CJ.

46:09.500 --> 46:12.250
Ah, you never told me
you had a kid.

46:12.375 --> 46:13.250
I don't have a kid.

46:13.375 --> 46:15.583
Are you blind?

46:15.708 --> 46:18.375
He's the spitting image of you
when you were his age.

46:18.500 --> 46:20.333
I think.

46:20.458 --> 46:23.125
Did, uh, Jeff mention
I abandoned him

46:23.250 --> 46:24.166
when he was four?

46:24.291 --> 46:25.333
Not yet, no, no.

46:25.458 --> 46:26.500
Good. Good.

46:26.625 --> 46:27.833
Well, come on in.

46:27.958 --> 46:29.833
Let's go.

46:29.958 --> 46:31.875
Hey, can you believe
he's still mad at me

46:32.000 --> 46:34.750
for something that happened
30 years ago?

46:34.875 --> 46:37.458
You dropped me off
in an orphanage for girls.

46:37.583 --> 46:40.625
And you're welcome.
[chuckles]

46:40.750 --> 46:43.125
Brian, [clears throat]
when--when his mom died,

46:43.250 --> 46:45.291
I mean, I just--I panicked.

46:45.416 --> 46:47.083
It was just me.

46:47.208 --> 46:49.875
I was young, stupid.

46:50.000 --> 46:53.625
I was afraid I was in
over my head being a dad,

46:53.750 --> 46:57.083
but kept tabs on you, didn't I?

46:57.208 --> 46:59.333
Here we go.
This is what I want to show you.

46:59.458 --> 47:00.791
Here we go.

47:00.916 --> 47:06.041
See, you two are dead ringers.

47:06.166 --> 47:10.708
Oh, look at my little Jeffy
with all his foster families.

47:10.833 --> 47:12.750
You're a lucky bastard.

47:12.875 --> 47:14.041
Well...

47:14.166 --> 47:15.375
He's not wrong.

47:15.500 --> 47:16.541
He looks just like you.

47:16.666 --> 47:20.125
CJ's my son?

47:20.250 --> 47:22.375
[soft, inquisitive music]

47:22.500 --> 47:23.458
What's going on here?

47:23.583 --> 47:24.583
How's that even possible?

47:24.708 --> 47:26.125
Do you even know
who his mom is?

47:26.250 --> 47:27.916
Due to my deep-seated
emotional issues,

47:28.041 --> 47:29.916
I've easily slept
with thousands and thousands

47:30.041 --> 47:31.208
and thousands of women.

47:31.333 --> 47:32.666
You're welcome.

47:32.791 --> 47:34.333
How many women
have you slept with, Dad?

47:34.458 --> 47:37.125
That's not your business.
That's none of your business.

47:37.250 --> 47:42.083
[music continues]

47:42.208 --> 47:44.083
So you're my son, little man.

47:46.458 --> 47:48.541
No wonder you're so handsome
and awesome.

47:48.666 --> 47:49.666
Hell yeah.

47:49.791 --> 47:51.333
We're gonna make
such a good team.

47:51.458 --> 47:52.583
We're gonna have
so much fun together.

47:52.708 --> 47:54.000
Up high.
[grunts]

47:54.125 --> 47:55.666
[laughs]

47:55.791 --> 47:56.833
Hey, Jeff.

47:58.833 --> 48:00.333
-Hey, Gordon.
-Yeah.

48:00.458 --> 48:02.708
Can I talk to you for a second?

48:02.833 --> 48:04.041
Look, um...

48:06.208 --> 48:08.916
we need a favor.

48:09.041 --> 48:10.291
These guys keep coming after us.

48:10.416 --> 48:13.000
It's not safe for the kids.

48:13.125 --> 48:15.166
Can we leave them here
for a bit?

48:15.291 --> 48:16.416
We're hoping you can look
after them for a while

48:16.541 --> 48:18.583
until we figure all this out.

48:18.708 --> 48:20.875
[poignant music]

48:21.000 --> 48:24.583
Yeah, um...

48:24.708 --> 48:25.916
Will you help me, Dad?

48:28.166 --> 48:30.958
I can't. Sorry...

48:33.583 --> 48:37.041
I'm just not that...guy.

48:38.458 --> 48:43.333
[music continues]

48:47.875 --> 48:49.083
[door opens]

48:58.041 --> 49:00.625
Oh, my God.

49:03.541 --> 49:04.541
You okay?

49:06.666 --> 49:09.416
Man, we gotta find out
why they did this to you.

49:09.541 --> 49:11.291
You know, why would anyone
want a kid from me?

49:14.541 --> 49:17.416
Why should I be a dad?

49:17.541 --> 49:19.375
You saw mine.

49:19.500 --> 49:21.041
That's why I enlisted.

49:21.166 --> 49:22.750
You know, I had my own team.

49:22.875 --> 49:24.875
Finally had a family.

49:25.000 --> 49:26.416
And I couldn't even
do that right.

49:26.541 --> 49:27.750
[muffled explosion]

49:27.875 --> 49:30.791
[muffled rapid gunfire]

49:30.916 --> 49:34.416
-[soft music]
-[shuddering breaths]

49:34.541 --> 49:36.750
[teammate's voice]
Sarge, what are you doing?

49:36.875 --> 49:38.083
Take him out!

49:39.541 --> 49:40.791
[Jeff's voice]
I couldn't do it,

49:40.916 --> 49:42.583
so they court-martialed me.

49:42.708 --> 49:43.541
[gavel thuds, echoes]

49:47.458 --> 49:50.541
You're still my
perfect soldier, Jeff.

49:50.666 --> 49:53.541
I wish I had more of you.

49:53.666 --> 49:55.083
Perfect soldier, my ass.

49:57.708 --> 49:59.333
That's not a flaw, man,
at all.

49:59.458 --> 50:01.541
I gotta be honest,
it sounds like that colonel guy,

50:01.666 --> 50:03.375
like he really liked you.

50:03.500 --> 50:05.750
Yeah, Colonel Kurtz.

50:05.875 --> 50:08.000
He always had my back.

50:08.125 --> 50:09.625
That's what it's all about, see?

50:11.625 --> 50:13.750
Letting them know
that we have their backs.

50:13.875 --> 50:15.666
[♪ Charlie Nguyen Kim:
"Rolling Memories"]

50:15.791 --> 50:17.458
♪ I got it, you got it ♪

50:17.583 --> 50:19.500
♪ Mm, they want it ♪

50:21.000 --> 50:21.916
[moans]

50:24.708 --> 50:25.583
[both moan]

50:25.708 --> 50:27.250
Wow, yeah.

50:27.375 --> 50:28.541
He's definitely your son.

50:29.833 --> 50:31.083
[both moan]

50:38.583 --> 50:39.666
What are you doing?

50:39.791 --> 50:41.541
Uh, nothing.
I mean, we just...

50:41.666 --> 50:42.625
It's kind of like
we eat the same thing.

50:42.750 --> 50:44.791
It's like, you know,
just like when you...

50:44.916 --> 50:47.041
You were eating [indistinct].

50:49.500 --> 50:52.083
We gotta figure out
why they did this to you.

50:52.208 --> 50:54.958
You don't know anyone
in that top secret...

50:55.083 --> 50:56.875
whatever?

50:57.000 --> 50:58.250
[ping sound]

51:00.416 --> 51:02.833
-Zach Galifianak-ish.
-Whoa, whoa.

51:02.958 --> 51:04.625
Easy, easy, easy.

51:04.750 --> 51:05.750
I'm good.

51:05.875 --> 51:06.875
[up-tempo music]

51:07.000 --> 51:08.791
How in the world
are we gonna find this guy?

51:08.916 --> 51:10.125
We're gonna pretend
to bang him.

51:10.250 --> 51:11.333
What?

51:14.083 --> 51:15.083
[car doors banging]

51:16.250 --> 51:17.708
Zach couldn't get women

51:17.833 --> 51:19.833
so he'd come to me to help him
with all his dating apps.

51:19.958 --> 51:21.458
Zach had no game.

51:21.583 --> 51:23.250
-Obviously, I do.
-Mm.

51:23.375 --> 51:26.083
So I'd pretend to be him
and text all these girls for him

51:26.208 --> 51:27.625
and I was amazing at it.

51:29.291 --> 51:30.250
Whoo-hoo!

51:30.375 --> 51:31.791
Daddy's back in business.

51:31.916 --> 51:33.416
Oh boy.

51:33.541 --> 51:35.041
This is the one.

51:35.166 --> 51:36.750
I can get this one.

51:36.875 --> 51:37.958
Why is that?

51:38.083 --> 51:40.750
Because she's half blind!

51:40.875 --> 51:42.875
She can't even see me.

51:43.000 --> 51:44.458
That's pretty sweet.

51:44.583 --> 51:47.333
Dude, is that my body?

51:47.458 --> 51:48.875
Yeah, yeah.
I should have asked.

51:49.000 --> 51:49.875
I got excited.

51:50.000 --> 51:50.916
[ping sound]

51:51.041 --> 51:52.000
[Jeff] And that's the plan.

51:52.125 --> 51:54.125
We're gonna catfish
this bag of shit.

51:54.250 --> 51:55.416
We don't need to find him.

51:55.541 --> 51:57.333
We're gonna bring him to us.

51:57.458 --> 52:00.916
And our fake profile
name will be...Candi.

52:01.041 --> 52:01.916
[phone beeps]

52:02.041 --> 52:03.041
Candi?

52:03.166 --> 52:04.458
What, you want
to call her Karen?

52:04.583 --> 52:05.750
-I like Candi, Dad.
-Would you just--

52:05.875 --> 52:09.500
Hey, just put your headphones on
and stop listening.

52:09.625 --> 52:10.750
You sit back.

52:10.875 --> 52:12.083
Let a master do the work.

52:12.208 --> 52:13.833
Okay.

52:13.958 --> 52:17.541
Well, hello, handsome sailor.

52:17.666 --> 52:19.708
[Siri's voice]
Well, hello handsome sailor.

52:19.833 --> 52:21.250
Ugh, here we go again.

52:21.375 --> 52:23.958
[Siri's voice] I just got
into town and you are hot.

52:24.083 --> 52:28.041
Russian bots.
Nice try, Putin.

52:28.166 --> 52:30.000
Blocked.

52:30.125 --> 52:31.041
[Siri's voice]
This user has blocked you.

52:31.166 --> 52:32.166
What?

52:32.291 --> 52:33.166
All right,
just give me the phone.

52:33.291 --> 52:35.083
-Give it to me, all right?
-Relax, Bri.

52:35.208 --> 52:37.791
Look, maybe this time you just
come in a little slower.

52:37.916 --> 52:41.666
Listen,
you wanna get smashed or what?

52:41.791 --> 52:42.750
Ugh.

52:42.875 --> 52:44.166
Report.

52:44.291 --> 52:45.458
[Siri's voice]
This user has reported you.

52:45.583 --> 52:46.666
What is his problem?

52:46.791 --> 52:48.041
Give me this thing.
You're done.

52:48.166 --> 52:49.250
What are you gonna do?

52:49.375 --> 52:50.375
I'm telling you
what I'm gonna do.

52:50.500 --> 52:52.583
I'm gonna come in nice
and slow, but steady.

52:52.708 --> 52:53.666
[computer beeps]

52:53.791 --> 52:55.000
[Siri's voice] Hi, I'm Emily.

52:55.125 --> 52:56.583
Nice to meet you.

52:56.708 --> 52:58.958
Oh, I'm on fire tonight.

52:59.083 --> 53:01.583
I just read your profile.

53:01.708 --> 53:05.958
I, too, am interested in...
Pterodactyls, bulimia,

53:06.083 --> 53:09.458
Love is Blind,
and the Mormon culture.

53:09.583 --> 53:11.000
Oh, this is so annoying.

53:12.250 --> 53:15.125
Yes, it seems
like we have much in common,

53:17.416 --> 53:19.583
but now
who's your favorite Mormon?

53:19.708 --> 53:20.958
Favorite Mormon?

53:21.083 --> 53:24.541
Favorite Mormon.
Uh...

53:24.666 --> 53:25.666
Top Gun Maverick.

53:25.791 --> 53:27.041
Not even a person.

53:27.166 --> 53:28.083
Jay-Z.

53:28.208 --> 53:29.583
[computer beeps]

53:29.708 --> 53:32.625
[Siri's voice] My favorite
Mormon is, of course, Jay-Z.

53:32.750 --> 53:34.083
Oh, she's the one.

53:34.208 --> 53:38.708
It is so nice to talk with
someone actually normal here.

53:38.833 --> 53:43.625
I hate when people come across
so disgusting and aggressive.

53:43.750 --> 53:47.250
Get your grubby thoughts
off of me, you know?

53:47.375 --> 53:48.500
Totally.

53:48.625 --> 53:50.416
So do you want
to get smashed or not?

53:50.541 --> 53:51.416
[notification beeps]

53:51.541 --> 53:52.666
Yeah.

53:52.791 --> 53:54.041
You see what I'm saying, Bri?

53:56.416 --> 54:01.750
You want to know
what really turns me on?

54:01.875 --> 54:03.583
[whimsical music]

54:03.708 --> 54:05.875
♪ I'm just a boy ♪

54:06.000 --> 54:08.875
♪ about to make love
to a woman ♪

54:09.000 --> 54:13.291
♪ about to make love
to a woman ♪

54:13.416 --> 54:16.000
♪ some call it intercourse ♪

54:17.791 --> 54:18.666
[scanner beeps]

54:19.833 --> 54:21.833
-Oh, no.
-Mm-hm.

54:21.958 --> 54:23.333
Oh, not again.

54:23.458 --> 54:25.416
-Sup, bitch?
-Got you, fool.

54:25.541 --> 54:27.416
Mmm, not going to jail.

54:27.541 --> 54:28.375
Eat shit, [indistinct].

54:28.500 --> 54:29.583
[screams]

54:30.666 --> 54:31.541
[sobs]

54:31.666 --> 54:32.583
Okay.

54:34.000 --> 54:37.750
You and I are gonna have
a very calm conversation.

54:40.333 --> 54:41.958
[shouts]
What did you do to my son?

54:42.083 --> 54:43.875
Dude, just please take
the hood off.

54:44.000 --> 54:45.583
I already know who you are,
dumbass.

54:45.708 --> 54:47.166
Oh, shit. Really?

54:47.291 --> 54:48.291
Yeah, Jeff.

54:48.416 --> 54:50.625
You're a pretty
specific looking guy.

54:50.750 --> 54:51.875
Damn it!

54:52.000 --> 54:53.708
[grunting]

54:55.083 --> 54:56.125
I want answers.

54:56.250 --> 54:57.875
Now.

54:58.000 --> 54:59.458
Start talking, bro.

54:59.583 --> 55:00.833
Uh-uh.

55:00.958 --> 55:02.583
Oh, you want to get
waterboarded?

55:02.708 --> 55:03.833
What?

55:03.958 --> 55:05.208
You asked for it.

55:05.333 --> 55:06.375
How are you gonna...?

55:06.500 --> 55:07.791
[ice rattles]

55:07.916 --> 55:09.416
That's not how you waterboard,
Jeff.

55:09.541 --> 55:10.708
That's right.

55:10.833 --> 55:12.750
What are you,
making me a protein shake?

55:12.875 --> 55:14.916
Be prepared to talk, bitch.

55:15.041 --> 55:18.208
-Not--Oh, come on.
-Are you thirsty?

55:18.333 --> 55:20.625
Yeah, how do you
like them apples?!

55:20.750 --> 55:21.791
Okay.

55:21.916 --> 55:23.083
Can I talk to you for a second?

55:23.208 --> 55:24.166
I was about to break him.

55:24.291 --> 55:25.375
Get over here.

55:27.166 --> 55:28.458
Ugh.

55:29.875 --> 55:31.041
Yes, Mom?

55:31.166 --> 55:33.791
Yeah, well,
what's going on over here,

55:33.916 --> 55:35.333
it's just not working,
okay?

55:35.458 --> 55:37.291
What?
When I almost killed him?

55:37.416 --> 55:38.875
You moisturized him
is what you did.

55:39.000 --> 55:40.500
Okay, so you're bad cop?

55:40.625 --> 55:41.958
-I can be bad cop.
-Okay.

55:42.083 --> 55:43.333
-You can do it, Dad.
-Yeah, I know.

55:43.458 --> 55:45.250
-Go get it out of him.
-I'll do it right now.

55:45.375 --> 55:46.583
What are we gonna do?

55:46.708 --> 55:47.916
What's that for?

55:48.041 --> 55:49.208
Torture his ass.

55:49.333 --> 55:50.250
[soft, quirky music]

55:50.375 --> 55:52.833
Reservoir Dogs.

55:52.958 --> 55:55.291
All right. Yeah, all right.

55:55.416 --> 55:56.416
I can't wait to see this.

55:56.541 --> 55:58.875
- Reservoir Dogs style.
-Yeah.

55:59.000 --> 56:00.875
[♪ Stealers Wheel:
“Stuck in the Middle”]

56:01.000 --> 56:02.375
Oh, God.

56:02.500 --> 56:04.125
Who's laughing now, bitch?

56:04.250 --> 56:08.000
♪ Well, I don't know
why I came here tonight ♪

56:08.125 --> 56:10.958
♪ I got the feeling that
Something ain't right ♪

56:11.083 --> 56:14.500
You look like Chris Christie
is on Dancing with the Stars.

56:16.083 --> 56:17.125
He's not--he's not scared.

56:17.250 --> 56:18.458
-He's not afraid.
-[Jeff] Don't be a quitter.

56:18.583 --> 56:20.208
Get back in there.

56:20.333 --> 56:21.208
Guess what?

56:22.500 --> 56:25.208
Playtime is over.

56:25.333 --> 56:29.166
[foreboding music]

56:29.291 --> 56:30.291
Oh.

56:35.458 --> 56:36.333
[music trails off]

56:37.625 --> 56:39.916
That's like
a traveling cosmetic kit.

56:40.041 --> 56:41.083
You bet it is.

56:41.208 --> 56:42.875
Pick your weapon, my friend.

56:43.000 --> 56:44.458
Uh, the toothbrush?

56:44.583 --> 56:45.708
Do you want this in you?

56:45.833 --> 56:46.833
Man, what?

56:46.958 --> 56:48.125
I'll start this way.
I don't care.

56:48.250 --> 56:49.666
Oh, my God,
stab him already.

56:49.791 --> 56:51.875
Look, the two boys over there

56:52.000 --> 56:54.500
would probably do
a better job interrogating me.

56:54.625 --> 56:57.208
Why don't you swap places
with them?

56:58.541 --> 57:01.208
Hey, look at me.

57:02.875 --> 57:06.541
You're making me look pathetic
in front of my kid, okay?

57:06.666 --> 57:08.500
I'm not gonna
tell you anything, okay?

57:08.625 --> 57:09.958
It doesn't matter
what you offer me.

57:10.083 --> 57:11.166
It doesn't matter
what you do to me.

57:11.291 --> 57:13.000
I'm not gonna tell you
what happened.

57:14.208 --> 57:15.250
Here's exactly what happened.

57:15.375 --> 57:17.166
So, how do I put this?

57:17.291 --> 57:21.083
That--that kid over there,
that's--that's not your son.

57:21.208 --> 57:23.125
Who somehow looks
a lot like you

57:23.250 --> 57:27.458
is because he is
a genetic analog of you.

57:27.583 --> 57:29.916
[Lucas] Genetic analog?

57:30.041 --> 57:31.000
You mean like a clone?

57:31.125 --> 57:32.541
Yeah. Smart kid.

57:32.666 --> 57:34.458
Clone.

57:34.583 --> 57:36.250
He's a genetic analog.
A clone.

57:36.375 --> 57:38.000
His name's CJ.

57:38.125 --> 57:41.041
That literally means
“Clone Jeff.”

57:43.166 --> 57:46.041
[somber music]

57:46.166 --> 57:48.458
So he's exactly like me?

57:48.583 --> 57:51.083
Well, modified version of you.

57:51.208 --> 57:54.291
See, he's faster, stronger,

57:54.416 --> 57:57.916
and way smarter than you, okay.

57:58.041 --> 57:59.333
He's a better version of you.

57:59.458 --> 58:00.916
You are community college.

58:01.041 --> 58:02.375
He is Harvard plus.

58:03.875 --> 58:04.833
Why would you do this?

58:04.958 --> 58:06.708
No, I didn't clone anyone.

58:06.833 --> 58:08.458
I'm just like a babysitter.

58:08.583 --> 58:09.541
[Brian] Then who did this?

58:09.666 --> 58:11.541
I--I--I can't tell you.

58:11.666 --> 58:13.625
All I got is a name
and I'm not telling you

58:13.750 --> 58:15.541
because they--ah, okay!

58:15.666 --> 58:17.333
It's Simon Maddox.

58:17.458 --> 58:18.416
Simon Maddox.

58:18.541 --> 58:20.750
Put down the lamp.
Simon Maddox.

58:20.875 --> 58:22.250
Who the hell is Simon Maddox?

58:22.375 --> 58:24.083
Oh, wow.

58:24.208 --> 58:27.333
You guys have no idea
what you just stepped into.

58:29.666 --> 58:33.500
[soft, tense music]

58:33.625 --> 58:35.541
[Brian] Okay.
Who is Simon Maddox?

58:37.666 --> 58:39.416
And why the hell
would he clone Jeff?

58:43.208 --> 58:46.791
[♪ Jay Ramsey: “Bayoue Belle”]

58:46.916 --> 58:52.000
[both] Ergh. Aaagh!

58:52.125 --> 58:53.875
Hah.

58:54.000 --> 58:58.916
♪ I used to sing and play the
blues in a little old band ♪

58:59.041 --> 59:04.458
♪ We got brave and we hit
the road in a '61 van ♪

59:04.583 --> 59:06.125
Wow, this guy's a genius.

59:08.708 --> 59:11.208
Oh man, super genius.

59:11.333 --> 59:12.375
Mm, mm, mm!

59:12.500 --> 59:13.958
Get that fight in there.
Mm, mm, mm!

59:14.083 --> 59:16.291
Oof. Okay.
Also super creepy.

59:17.583 --> 59:18.958
♪ Fourteen dollars
in the kitty ♪

59:19.083 --> 59:22.833
♪ when we left Folger City
and we headed down south ♪

59:22.958 --> 59:24.375
[both] Whoa.

59:24.500 --> 59:28.541
You can read my mind?

59:28.666 --> 59:32.583
Yes. Crazy.

59:35.208 --> 59:39.125
♪ I turned toward the swamp
to look around ♪

59:39.250 --> 59:40.958
Hah! Hah!

59:41.083 --> 59:43.208
♪ Bayou Belle give
your guitar heck ♪

59:43.333 --> 59:44.875
Wait, I got an idea.

59:46.458 --> 59:49.083
Alexa, play some
old-school hip-hop.

59:49.208 --> 59:50.500
[♪ Ice Cube: “You Can Do It
(Feat. Mack 10, Ms. Toi)"]

59:50.625 --> 59:52.166
♪ Ninety-nine, baby ♪

59:52.291 --> 59:53.833
♪ I'm on the grind, baby ♪

59:55.000 --> 59:56.041
♪ Show me something ♪

59:56.166 --> 59:58.291
♪ You can do it
put your back into it ♪

59:58.416 --> 59:59.791
♪ I can do it
put your into it... ♪

59:59.916 --> 01:00:01.583
Sick.

01:00:01.708 --> 01:00:03.791
♪ Tic-tic-boom, hear me banging
down these back streets ♪

01:00:03.916 --> 01:00:06.166
♪ Bumpin' Blackstreet
treated like an athlete ♪

01:00:06.291 --> 01:00:07.875
♪ we be clubbing
till the day we die ♪

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:09.708
♪ ask the bartender
if you think we lie... ♪

01:00:09.833 --> 01:00:11.041
[phone ringing]

01:00:11.166 --> 01:00:12.625
[whispers] Crap.

01:00:12.750 --> 01:00:15.666
Hey, Em,
we're running a little bit late.

01:00:15.791 --> 01:00:16.791
That's all, hon.

01:00:16.916 --> 01:00:18.791
-[man breathes over phone]
-Em?

01:00:18.916 --> 01:00:20.375
♪ You can do it
put your back into it ♪

01:00:20.500 --> 01:00:22.166
Em?

01:00:22.291 --> 01:00:25.083
[man's voice]
[sighs] Look at your screen.

01:00:25.208 --> 01:00:30.083
[foreboding music]

01:00:32.541 --> 01:00:35.041
[man's voice] Would you like us
to follow Emily home?

01:00:35.166 --> 01:00:36.750
Pay her a little visit?

01:00:36.875 --> 01:00:39.541
No. Would not like that.

01:00:39.666 --> 01:00:42.083
[man's voice]
Then you bring the boy to us.

01:00:42.208 --> 01:00:44.958
Drive to the coordinates
that we send to you.

01:00:45.083 --> 01:00:48.208
Otherwise, we will
visit your wife.

01:00:48.333 --> 01:00:50.166
[screeches, phone beeping]

01:00:56.041 --> 01:00:59.583
[gentle music]

01:00:59.708 --> 01:01:01.958
[unsettling music]

01:01:02.083 --> 01:01:03.208
[Jeff] You see, Bri-Bri?

01:01:03.333 --> 01:01:04.791
How much fun are you
having right now?

01:01:04.916 --> 01:01:06.875
Whooh! God, you're good.

01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:09.083
So how'd you track down
this Simon Maddox?

01:01:09.208 --> 01:01:11.000
You do your forensic accounting?

01:01:11.125 --> 01:01:12.041
Hm.

01:01:12.166 --> 01:01:13.833
[Lucas giggles]

01:01:13.958 --> 01:01:16.125
Bri-Bri? You okay?

01:01:16.250 --> 01:01:18.500
Oh, yeah, yeah.

01:01:18.625 --> 01:01:19.541
Okay.

01:01:22.541 --> 01:01:24.500
Man, it's finally happening.

01:01:24.625 --> 01:01:26.625
CJ and I
are finally connecting.

01:01:26.750 --> 01:01:28.541
Isn't this incredible?

01:01:28.666 --> 01:01:30.625
It is, yeah.

01:01:30.750 --> 01:01:35.250
Hey, I gotta thank you
for that little talk earlier.

01:01:35.375 --> 01:01:37.000
I think you're right.

01:01:37.125 --> 01:01:38.666
I really am gonna
be the best dad.

01:01:42.416 --> 01:01:43.625
-[woman screams]
-[man 2's voice] He's got a gun!

01:01:43.750 --> 01:01:45.000
[man 3's voice] Oh, my God!
They're gonna kill her!

01:01:45.125 --> 01:01:46.083
[Jeff]
So how much further, Bri-Bri?

01:01:46.208 --> 01:01:47.083
[dramatic thud]
[scream echoes]

01:01:48.583 --> 01:01:50.375
No, no, not--not much.

01:01:50.500 --> 01:01:53.333
Man, I can't wait to see
this ass-hat face-to-face.

01:01:53.458 --> 01:01:54.333
Right, CJ?

01:01:54.458 --> 01:01:55.375
Right.

01:01:56.500 --> 01:01:57.583
[Lucas giggling]

01:01:57.708 --> 01:02:02.625
[tense music]

01:02:11.166 --> 01:02:13.833
[car rumbling, stops]

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:18.458
[car doors banging]

01:02:18.583 --> 01:02:20.041
[Jeff]
Huh, this can't be right.

01:02:20.166 --> 01:02:22.458
Pictured it more of like
an Area 51 type place.

01:02:24.291 --> 01:02:26.375
Maybe you did your
forensicing wrong.

01:02:27.541 --> 01:02:33.416
[car revving]

01:02:33.541 --> 01:02:36.375
-Lucas, get in the van.
-Why?

01:02:36.500 --> 01:02:37.833
[Brian] Get in the van
right now, please.

01:02:39.250 --> 01:02:42.208
Bri? What's going on?

01:02:42.333 --> 01:02:44.375
[suspenseful music]

01:02:44.500 --> 01:02:46.416
Jeff, I'm so sorry.

01:02:46.541 --> 01:02:47.458
For what?

01:02:47.583 --> 01:02:48.500
[gunman] Get down!

01:02:48.625 --> 01:02:50.083
[gunman] Freeze!
Don't you move!

01:02:51.958 --> 01:02:54.333
Dude, they were coming
after Emily, all right?

01:02:54.458 --> 01:02:56.958
They were firing guns
and--and everything, man.

01:02:57.083 --> 01:02:59.333
I--I--I didn't know what to do.

01:02:59.458 --> 01:03:04.291
[♪ Pretti Emage: “Earthquake”]

01:03:04.416 --> 01:03:05.416
♪ Shake that, shake that ♪

01:03:05.541 --> 01:03:06.916
♪ Shake that, shake that
go at best ♪

01:03:07.041 --> 01:03:07.958
♪ Shake that, shake that ♪

01:03:08.083 --> 01:03:08.958
♪ Make it jiggle
make it jiggle ♪

01:03:09.083 --> 01:03:10.333
♪ Do a jump, split ♪

01:03:10.458 --> 01:03:11.458
♪ Make it wiggle
Make it wiggle ♪

01:03:11.583 --> 01:03:12.458
♪ Make that, make that ♪

01:03:12.583 --> 01:03:13.416
♪ Wanna shake it? ♪

01:03:13.541 --> 01:03:14.541
♪ Wanna... ♪

01:03:17.000 --> 01:03:18.750
Who the hell are you?

01:03:18.875 --> 01:03:22.250
Oh, you already know my name.

01:03:22.375 --> 01:03:25.208
What's that?
Captain Dickface?

01:03:25.333 --> 01:03:27.291
No.

01:03:27.416 --> 01:03:29.166
This is Simon Maddox.

01:03:32.375 --> 01:03:33.875
[dramatic music]

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:35.458
Hey, you touch him
and I'll kill you!

01:03:37.500 --> 01:03:38.583
Don't touch him!

01:03:44.083 --> 01:03:45.416
Why are you doing this?

01:03:45.541 --> 01:03:47.041
Why are you doing this anyway?

01:03:48.291 --> 01:03:49.708
He's just a kid.

01:03:49.833 --> 01:03:53.416
He is not just a kid.

01:03:53.541 --> 01:03:54.708
Why me?

01:03:56.333 --> 01:03:57.541
Why'd you do this to me?

01:04:00.250 --> 01:04:01.833
I'm not the one
who can answer that.

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:05.000
Come on, CJ.

01:04:05.125 --> 01:04:06.291
-Wait, hold on.
-[automatic rifle cocks]

01:04:06.416 --> 01:04:07.708
Hold on.

01:04:08.916 --> 01:04:11.000
Let me at least
say goodbye to him.

01:04:11.125 --> 01:04:13.083
Trust me, this is harder
for you than it is for him.

01:04:15.250 --> 01:04:19.250
CJ isn't capable of making
any emotional connections.

01:04:19.375 --> 01:04:22.708
It's literally not in his DNA.

01:04:22.833 --> 01:04:24.041
Well, that's bullshit.

01:04:25.375 --> 01:04:26.333
I'll prove it.

01:04:31.500 --> 01:04:32.500
Hey.

01:04:35.083 --> 01:04:36.916
I love you, little man.

01:04:37.041 --> 01:04:39.791
And I know you love me, too.

01:04:39.916 --> 01:04:41.958
I don't know what you mean.

01:04:42.083 --> 01:04:43.583
What does love mean?

01:04:45.416 --> 01:04:46.958
It's in your heart.

01:04:49.500 --> 01:04:51.833
Don't you feel anything
in your heart?

01:04:51.958 --> 01:04:53.083
No?

01:04:55.916 --> 01:04:58.958
Do you feel anything at all?

01:04:59.083 --> 01:05:00.250
No.

01:05:04.708 --> 01:05:06.125
I don't believe that.

01:05:07.291 --> 01:05:10.250
So this isn't goodbye, okay?

01:05:10.375 --> 01:05:11.791
I'll see you again real soon.

01:05:14.416 --> 01:05:15.666
Up high.

01:05:19.666 --> 01:05:20.875
Ah, come on.

01:05:22.708 --> 01:05:23.666
Don't leave me hanging, dude.

01:05:23.791 --> 01:05:24.875
Not now.

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:28.083
Please.

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:33.083
[Lucas] CJ!

01:05:34.666 --> 01:05:36.000
Lu--Lucas.

01:05:44.750 --> 01:05:46.916
[rhythmic drum beating]

01:05:47.041 --> 01:05:48.041
Lucas, let's go.

01:05:48.166 --> 01:05:53.166
[poignant music]

01:05:53.291 --> 01:05:54.833
[indistinct radio chatter]

01:05:57.000 --> 01:06:01.458
[cars revving]

01:06:01.583 --> 01:06:02.458
[dramatic strings]

01:06:04.708 --> 01:06:06.125
Lucas, get in the van.

01:06:07.208 --> 01:06:11.083
[tense music]

01:06:15.541 --> 01:06:19.750
[gentle music]

01:06:19.875 --> 01:06:21.000
♪ This is the rhythm
of the night ♪

01:06:21.125 --> 01:06:23.166
[laughs]
How do you like me now?

01:06:23.291 --> 01:06:25.083
Ooh! Ooh!

01:06:33.541 --> 01:06:36.083
Oh, did I get him?

01:06:36.208 --> 01:06:38.500
Did...did I look cool?

01:06:38.625 --> 01:06:40.083
No.

01:06:40.208 --> 01:06:44.833
But you distracted him,
and then Jeff took him out.

01:06:44.958 --> 01:06:46.916
Oh.

01:06:47.041 --> 01:06:50.666
Hey, Lucas, I'm sorry.

01:06:50.791 --> 01:06:52.666
Look, I'm just...

01:06:52.791 --> 01:06:58.000
I just may not be the dad
you...you need or you...

01:06:58.125 --> 01:06:59.875
I mean, the one you really want.

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:01.166
What do you mean?

01:07:01.291 --> 01:07:02.375
I'm not young.

01:07:03.541 --> 01:07:04.541
You know, I'm not badass.

01:07:04.666 --> 01:07:06.416
I'm just not a...

01:07:06.541 --> 01:07:09.125
You are my dad.

01:07:09.250 --> 01:07:11.083
I don't want you
to change at all.

01:07:13.041 --> 01:07:13.875
You don't?

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:14.958
No.

01:07:16.333 --> 01:07:20.583
I have you, right?

01:07:20.708 --> 01:07:21.916
Right.

01:07:29.041 --> 01:07:31.583
Hey, Jeff, should I tie him up
and torture his ass

01:07:31.708 --> 01:07:33.083
like we did
with the fat leprechaun?

01:07:33.208 --> 01:07:34.333
Would you?

01:07:34.458 --> 01:07:35.500
I need a moment to recover

01:07:35.625 --> 01:07:38.041
from your dad's
gut-wrenching betrayal.

01:07:38.166 --> 01:07:40.500
I'm--I'm really sorry,
all right?

01:07:40.625 --> 01:07:42.083
Doesn't matter.

01:07:42.208 --> 01:07:43.125
I failed.

01:07:43.250 --> 01:07:44.791
You--you didn't fail him.

01:07:44.916 --> 01:07:45.958
We gotta go get him.

01:07:46.083 --> 01:07:48.125
Didn't you hear what he said?

01:07:48.250 --> 01:07:49.250
He doesn't care about me.

01:07:49.375 --> 01:07:51.000
Okay, so that's it.

01:07:51.125 --> 01:07:53.000
After all we've been through?

01:07:53.125 --> 01:07:54.208
Whatever.

01:07:54.333 --> 01:07:55.458
He doesn't want me
to come get him.

01:07:55.583 --> 01:07:58.041
Of course he wants you to come.

01:07:58.166 --> 01:07:59.833
Listen to me.
Hey! Listen to me!

01:07:59.958 --> 01:08:02.208
You're not your dad.
Okay?

01:08:02.333 --> 01:08:03.166
You know how I know this?

01:08:05.333 --> 01:08:08.416
I know you got heart.

01:08:08.541 --> 01:08:09.833
Careful, Bri.

01:08:11.166 --> 01:08:12.375
You're starting to talk
like we're best friends.

01:08:12.500 --> 01:08:14.083
Nah, closer but...

01:08:14.208 --> 01:08:15.583
[phone beeps, vibrating]

01:08:15.708 --> 01:08:16.625
[feet thumps]

01:08:19.875 --> 01:08:21.000
[tense music]

01:08:21.125 --> 01:08:22.291
[phone beeping]

01:08:24.000 --> 01:08:25.125
It's your phone.

01:08:26.582 --> 01:08:28.707
Lucas, w--where's the tracker?

01:08:28.832 --> 01:08:31.082
Well, it's in my hood--

01:08:31.207 --> 01:08:32.207
CJ has it.

01:08:32.332 --> 01:08:33.166
I thought you shut it off?

01:08:33.291 --> 01:08:35.041
I did.

01:08:35.166 --> 01:08:36.457
You know what this means?

01:08:36.582 --> 01:08:38.166
-What?
-Why don't you tell him, Luke?

01:08:38.291 --> 01:08:39.625
It means he turned
the tracker on

01:08:39.750 --> 01:08:41.125
because he wants you
to go save him.

01:08:42.332 --> 01:08:43.750
How do we know
that's what he wants?

01:08:43.875 --> 01:08:45.082
Because you're his dad.

01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:48.375
Damn right, I am.

01:08:48.500 --> 01:08:52.291
[intense music]

01:08:52.416 --> 01:08:55.207
[phone beeping rapidly]

01:08:57.250 --> 01:09:00.750
[foreboding music]

01:09:07.541 --> 01:09:08.791
Oh, this is where you worked?

01:09:08.916 --> 01:09:10.582
-[Jeff] Mm-hm.
-[Brian] It's like a lab.

01:09:10.707 --> 01:09:12.000
Why would they bring him
back here?

01:09:12.125 --> 01:09:13.625
This guy's a freaking nerd.

01:09:13.750 --> 01:09:17.541
[insects chirping]

01:09:17.666 --> 01:09:18.707
[car doors banging]

01:09:21.500 --> 01:09:23.207
Lucas, I need you to stay
in the van

01:09:23.332 --> 01:09:25.500
and lock the door, okay?

01:09:25.625 --> 01:09:27.832
Lucas, I want to keep
you safe, all right?

01:09:27.957 --> 01:09:30.166
That's the most important thing
to me, okay?

01:09:30.291 --> 01:09:34.582
Okay, but you're gonna
come back, though, right?

01:09:34.707 --> 01:09:36.207
Of course we're coming back.

01:09:36.332 --> 01:09:37.541
Right, Jeff?

01:09:37.666 --> 01:09:38.750
Both of us?

01:09:39.832 --> 01:09:41.832
Sure.

01:09:41.957 --> 01:09:43.125
Let's do this.

01:09:43.250 --> 01:09:46.707
[dramatic action music]

01:09:46.832 --> 01:09:50.250
[fence clanking]

01:09:50.375 --> 01:09:51.250
[button beeping]

01:09:51.375 --> 01:09:52.291
[Brian] Oh.

01:09:52.416 --> 01:09:53.625
[gate hinges creak]

01:09:53.750 --> 01:09:54.708
Really?

01:09:54.833 --> 01:09:56.125
Quit screwing around.

01:10:03.458 --> 01:10:05.416
Hey,
why--why is the door open?

01:10:05.541 --> 01:10:07.375
It's like they're expecting us.

01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:11.708
[phone beeping]

01:10:24.041 --> 01:10:25.791
[phone beeping]

01:10:25.916 --> 01:10:27.625
[rapid beeping, static]

01:10:35.625 --> 01:10:37.625
I don't know.
What are you doing?

01:10:37.750 --> 01:10:38.666
Split up
and cover more ground.

01:10:38.791 --> 01:10:39.791
You gotta say that to me, okay?

01:10:39.916 --> 01:10:41.333
That's what I just said.
I was--

01:10:41.458 --> 01:10:42.333
You didn't. [indistinct]
with your freaking hands.

01:10:42.458 --> 01:10:44.041
-I did not--
-Stop with the hands.

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:52.875
[suspenseful music]

01:10:54.500 --> 01:10:55.708
[dramatic strings]

01:11:03.625 --> 01:11:08.458
[suspenseful music continues]

01:11:12.500 --> 01:11:13.583
[dramatic thud]

01:11:16.333 --> 01:11:17.958
-Oh, my God!
-Hi.

01:11:18.083 --> 01:11:21.083
CJ, you scared the crap
out of me.

01:11:21.208 --> 01:11:22.458
That's a weird outfit.

01:11:22.583 --> 01:11:24.958
Well, that's easier
than I thought.

01:11:25.083 --> 01:11:27.041
Let's call your dad.

01:11:27.166 --> 01:11:29.291
-[Jeff] Hey, what's up?
- Found CJ, huh?

01:11:29.416 --> 01:11:31.125
How about that, huh?

01:11:31.250 --> 01:11:32.291
-[Jeff] How's that possible?
- What are you talking about?

01:11:32.416 --> 01:11:35.250
What, you think you're the only
one that could be the, uh...

01:11:35.375 --> 01:11:36.541
hero?

01:11:36.666 --> 01:11:38.375
[dramatic strings]

01:11:39.541 --> 01:11:42.125
Wait, there's two CJs?

01:11:42.250 --> 01:11:43.166
[Brian] This is insane.

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:46.750
Which one's ours?

01:11:46.875 --> 01:11:48.208
I don't know.

01:11:50.458 --> 01:11:51.791
Hey, little dudes.

01:11:51.916 --> 01:11:53.916
Which one of you two
is my little guy?

01:11:55.625 --> 01:11:57.416
Whoa, whoa, hey! Guys! Guys!

01:11:57.541 --> 01:12:00.166
Hey, chill!

01:12:00.291 --> 01:12:01.250
Bitch!

01:12:01.375 --> 01:12:03.041
[upbeat music]

01:12:03.166 --> 01:12:04.166
[screaming]

01:12:08.416 --> 01:12:10.125
[strains]

01:12:10.250 --> 01:12:12.125
[groans]

01:12:12.250 --> 01:12:13.375
That was a little excessive,
huh?

01:12:13.500 --> 01:12:15.000
It was self-defense!

01:12:16.250 --> 01:12:17.125
[dramatic strings]

01:12:18.666 --> 01:12:19.625
What are they, possessed?

01:12:19.750 --> 01:12:20.916
No, no, I'm not...

01:12:21.041 --> 01:12:22.125
I don't like
where this is going.

01:12:22.250 --> 01:12:23.791
I'm out.

01:12:23.916 --> 01:12:25.125
Oh, gosh.

01:12:25.250 --> 01:12:26.708
[security alarm blaring]

01:12:26.833 --> 01:12:27.958
What the hell.

01:12:30.041 --> 01:12:33.083
[Jeff] Oh, come on.

01:12:33.208 --> 01:12:34.208
[clone CJs growl]

01:12:34.333 --> 01:12:35.791
-Okay.
-Nope.

01:12:36.958 --> 01:12:41.208
No. No. No.

01:12:42.958 --> 01:12:44.083
[rope whooshes]

01:12:45.416 --> 01:12:47.458
What the hell is going on here?

01:12:47.583 --> 01:12:48.958
All right,
everyone needs to just relax.

01:12:49.083 --> 01:12:51.708
-No, no, no, no, no, no.
-Relax! Relax.

01:12:51.833 --> 01:12:53.125
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

01:12:53.250 --> 01:12:54.250
Go, go, go, go!

01:12:54.375 --> 01:12:56.750
[CJs screaming]

01:12:57.875 --> 01:12:59.708
-No!
-Sorry.

01:12:59.833 --> 01:13:01.750
Ah, you gotta help me!

01:13:01.875 --> 01:13:03.291
-Sorry.
-He's biting me.

01:13:04.791 --> 01:13:06.458
Jeff, I can't see.
Get him off!

01:13:06.583 --> 01:13:07.541
[strains]

01:13:07.666 --> 01:13:08.750
-[groans]
-I'm so sorry.

01:13:08.875 --> 01:13:10.416
Why are you apologizing?

01:13:10.541 --> 01:13:12.375
For beating the shit
out of little versions of me.

01:13:13.666 --> 01:13:15.083
I have no one
to talk to about it.

01:13:15.208 --> 01:13:16.583
Stop it! Stop it!
I don't like that.

01:13:16.708 --> 01:13:18.291
Just punch him and apologize.

01:13:19.458 --> 01:13:22.666
I'm so sorry.
I'm very sorry.

01:13:22.791 --> 01:13:23.791
Oh, God.

01:13:25.708 --> 01:13:28.166
[dramatic music]

01:13:28.291 --> 01:13:30.166
I can't believe
they cloned that many.

01:13:30.291 --> 01:13:31.541
What assholes.

01:13:31.666 --> 01:13:32.541
There's a lot of them.

01:13:32.666 --> 01:13:37.041
[distant loud thudding]

01:13:37.166 --> 01:13:39.000
You, uh...

01:13:39.125 --> 01:13:40.166
You hear that?

01:13:40.291 --> 01:13:41.708
Yeah.

01:13:41.833 --> 01:13:42.916
What is that?

01:13:43.041 --> 01:13:45.250
I don't know.

01:13:45.375 --> 01:13:46.458
A T-rex?

01:13:52.041 --> 01:13:53.583
-[loud thud]
-[glass clanks]

01:13:54.916 --> 01:13:59.500
-[suspenseful music]
-[loud thudding]

01:14:05.083 --> 01:14:06.750
[clone CJs screaming]

01:14:06.875 --> 01:14:07.958
[♪ “Ride of the Valkyries
(from Die Walküre, Act III)”]

01:14:08.083 --> 01:14:11.250
Oh...Oh...Oh, my God!

01:14:11.375 --> 01:14:13.500
[clone CJ] Get some! Get some!

01:14:15.750 --> 01:14:17.041
[♪ “Ride of the Valkyries
(from Die Walküre, Act III)”]

01:14:17.166 --> 01:14:19.208
Oh, shit.

01:14:19.333 --> 01:14:23.125
[indistinct]

01:14:23.250 --> 01:14:27.333
[♪ “Ride of the Valkyries
(from Die Walküre, Act III)”]

01:14:30.041 --> 01:14:31.375
No, no, no, no!

01:14:31.500 --> 01:14:33.083
[panting]

01:14:35.041 --> 01:14:39.125
[distant clatter, explosion]

01:14:40.333 --> 01:14:41.750
[distant screaming]

01:14:41.875 --> 01:14:44.041
[electricity crackling]

01:14:44.166 --> 01:14:46.541
[gentle, quirky music]

01:14:46.666 --> 01:14:48.166
Thelma and Louise?

01:14:50.416 --> 01:14:51.416
We have to hold hands?

01:14:51.541 --> 01:14:53.375
Yeah, we gotta hold hands.

01:14:59.083 --> 01:15:03.958
[gentle uplifting music]

01:15:08.291 --> 01:15:09.416
What the hell.

01:15:12.875 --> 01:15:15.541
[clattering]

01:15:15.666 --> 01:15:18.166
[distant screaming]

01:15:19.541 --> 01:15:22.250
[screaming]

01:15:22.375 --> 01:15:24.833
[invisible wall crackling]

01:15:26.250 --> 01:15:28.416
[clones groaning]

01:15:29.875 --> 01:15:31.750
It's like they got
dog collars on, look at...

01:15:31.875 --> 01:15:33.333
Look at them.

01:15:33.458 --> 01:15:36.041
It's an electric fence.
They can't get past here.

01:15:36.166 --> 01:15:38.208
It's incredible.

01:15:38.333 --> 01:15:40.458
-[laughing]
-Yes!

01:15:42.375 --> 01:15:44.166
Idiots! What's up now?

01:15:44.291 --> 01:15:45.375
-Yeah, now!
-What's up now?

01:15:45.500 --> 01:15:46.666
[Brian] What's up now?

01:15:46.791 --> 01:15:49.416
-Suck it!
-Yeah! That's what he said!

01:15:49.541 --> 01:15:51.250
[gun thuds, cocks]

01:15:51.375 --> 01:15:53.166
Okay, okay.

01:15:55.666 --> 01:15:56.833
Hey, Bri.

01:15:56.958 --> 01:15:58.125
Remember what Jenny
said to Forrest

01:15:58.250 --> 01:15:59.166
when he was gimping around

01:15:59.291 --> 01:16:01.833
with those metal things
on his legs?

01:16:01.958 --> 01:16:03.083
No.

01:16:04.333 --> 01:16:05.666
[masked man grunts]

01:16:05.791 --> 01:16:07.708
Run, Forrest! Run!

01:16:07.833 --> 01:16:09.041
[gunshot]

01:16:10.666 --> 01:16:11.541
[door bangs]

01:16:11.666 --> 01:16:12.625
God.

01:16:14.625 --> 01:16:15.666
Ugh.

01:16:15.791 --> 01:16:17.583
‘Sup dawg?

01:16:21.125 --> 01:16:22.333
Hello, Jeff.

01:16:24.541 --> 01:16:26.875
Lucas! Lucas!

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:28.041
-We gotta go!
-Dad!

01:16:28.166 --> 01:16:30.208
-We gotta go!
-Wh--what's happening?

01:16:30.333 --> 01:16:31.333
Where's Jeff?

01:16:33.083 --> 01:16:35.041
Colonel?

01:16:35.166 --> 01:16:36.750
What are you doing
with this freakin' nerd?

01:16:36.875 --> 01:16:37.916
Why don't you just shut
your face, you loser.

01:16:38.041 --> 01:16:39.250
I own a Bugatti, okay?

01:16:39.375 --> 01:16:41.000
I get tons of hot chicks now.

01:16:41.125 --> 01:16:43.750
I see you two have become pals.

01:16:43.875 --> 01:16:45.583
What the hell's going on here?

01:16:45.708 --> 01:16:49.750
Well, after all you've done
for us, Jeff,

01:16:49.875 --> 01:16:51.166
you deserve some answers now.

01:16:51.291 --> 01:16:53.916
Yeah. Why'd you do this to me?

01:16:54.041 --> 01:16:57.458
Because you were
my perfect soldier.

01:16:57.583 --> 01:17:00.166
A true physical specimen.

01:17:00.291 --> 01:17:04.666
But do you know
what your kryptonite is?

01:17:04.791 --> 01:17:06.166
Gefilte fish?

01:17:06.291 --> 01:17:10.125
You have too much...empathy.

01:17:10.250 --> 01:17:11.500
[doorbell rings, opens]

01:17:11.625 --> 01:17:14.708
[somber music]

01:17:14.833 --> 01:17:18.500
CJ. You okay?

01:17:20.958 --> 01:17:23.541
See, son,
you weren't the only soldier

01:17:23.666 --> 01:17:27.583
to let your country down
in the field.

01:17:27.708 --> 01:17:29.041
Soldiers get tired.

01:17:30.625 --> 01:17:34.666
They get afraid
and start to have feelings.

01:17:34.791 --> 01:17:38.833
Well, I needed
to fix that problem.

01:17:38.958 --> 01:17:42.416
So when I stumbled
upon Simon's genius here...

01:17:42.541 --> 01:17:44.250
Genius, bitch.

01:17:44.375 --> 01:17:49.208
Even Simon didn't realize what
his technology could create.

01:17:49.333 --> 01:17:53.000
It could create
the perfect genetic soldier.

01:17:53.125 --> 01:17:57.791
All we needed
was your superior DNA.

01:17:57.916 --> 01:17:59.666
Random drug tests.

01:17:59.791 --> 01:18:02.500
You were our ideal candidate,
Jeff.

01:18:02.625 --> 01:18:05.500
So you're telling me
all those little guys out there

01:18:05.625 --> 01:18:08.833
are going to be super soldiers?

01:18:10.583 --> 01:18:15.083
Each one designed
to never get tired.

01:18:15.208 --> 01:18:17.583
And now for one final test.

01:18:20.291 --> 01:18:21.750
[somber music]

01:18:21.875 --> 01:18:24.125
Go ahead, CJ.

01:18:24.250 --> 01:18:26.041
Do what you were trained to do.

01:18:27.958 --> 01:18:31.291
Sergeant Eamon,
thank you for your service.

01:18:31.416 --> 01:18:32.291
[crossbow clanks]

01:18:38.083 --> 01:18:40.458
CJ...listen, man.

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:44.458
Yeah, I...

01:18:44.583 --> 01:18:46.791
you're not a machine.

01:18:46.916 --> 01:18:49.625
You know how I know that?

01:18:49.750 --> 01:18:51.791
Because if we're the same,

01:18:51.916 --> 01:18:53.916
it means we got the same heart.

01:18:55.541 --> 01:18:58.083
[soft, tense music swells,
fades]

01:18:59.375 --> 01:19:02.583
[dramatic music]

01:19:02.708 --> 01:19:04.291
[Maddox]
[slow motion] Fuck!

01:19:04.416 --> 01:19:06.250
[dramatic choral]

01:19:06.375 --> 01:19:07.250
[groans]

01:19:07.375 --> 01:19:08.458
[body thumps]

01:19:08.583 --> 01:19:10.750
[soldiers screaming]

01:19:10.875 --> 01:19:13.416
[♪ KC & The Sunshine Band:
“Give It Up”]

01:19:13.541 --> 01:19:16.583
♪ Everybody wants you ♪

01:19:16.708 --> 01:19:20.458
♪ Everybody wants your love ♪

01:19:20.583 --> 01:19:23.208
♪ I'd just like to make
you mine... ♪

01:19:23.333 --> 01:19:24.250
[strains]

01:19:25.458 --> 01:19:26.500
[CJ strains]

01:19:26.625 --> 01:19:28.083
[screams]

01:19:28.208 --> 01:19:30.625
♪ Na-na, na-na, na-na,
na-na-na-na now ♪

01:19:30.750 --> 01:19:32.166
♪ Baby, give it up ♪

01:19:32.291 --> 01:19:33.291
♪ Give it up ♪

01:19:33.416 --> 01:19:35.833
♪ Baby, give it up ♪

01:19:35.958 --> 01:19:38.166
♪ Na-na, na-na, na-na,
na-na-na-na now ♪

01:19:38.291 --> 01:19:40.000
-[ping sound]
-♪ Baby, give it up ♪

01:19:40.125 --> 01:19:41.250
♪ Give it up ♪

01:19:41.375 --> 01:19:43.125
♪ Baby, give it up ♪

01:19:49.375 --> 01:19:51.125
[body thumps]

01:19:51.250 --> 01:19:54.958
-[ping sound]
-♪ Everybody sees you ♪

01:19:55.083 --> 01:19:57.916
♪ Everybody looks and stares ♪

01:19:58.041 --> 01:20:01.500
[soft, dramatic music]

01:20:01.625 --> 01:20:03.625
♪ Na-na, na-na, na-na,
na-na-na-na now ♪

01:20:03.750 --> 01:20:05.041
♪ Baby, give it up ♪

01:20:05.166 --> 01:20:06.416
♪ Give it up ♪

01:20:06.541 --> 01:20:08.750
♪ Baby, give it up ♪

01:20:08.875 --> 01:20:11.291
♪ Na-na, na-na, na-na,
na-na-na-na now ♪

01:20:11.416 --> 01:20:12.750
♪ Baby, give it up ♪

01:20:12.875 --> 01:20:14.125
♪ Give it up ♪

01:20:14.250 --> 01:20:16.333
♪ Baby, give it up ♪♪

01:20:16.458 --> 01:20:21.333
[dramatic music]

01:20:26.166 --> 01:20:27.083
[gun clicks]

01:20:27.208 --> 01:20:29.791
You broke my heart.

01:20:29.916 --> 01:20:31.750
[Brian] Ha-ha.
How do you like me now?!

01:20:31.875 --> 01:20:33.041
♪ This is the rhythm
of the night ♪

01:20:33.166 --> 01:20:34.416
Ooh!

01:20:37.000 --> 01:20:38.041
Did I get him?

01:20:38.166 --> 01:20:39.333
-[air bag hisses]
-Ooh.

01:20:40.541 --> 01:20:41.416
[Colonel Kurtz grunts]

01:20:41.541 --> 01:20:42.750
[body thumps]

01:20:44.041 --> 01:20:46.666
[groans] How'd I do?

01:20:46.791 --> 01:20:48.416
Did I look cool?

01:20:48.541 --> 01:20:50.041
You did, Dad.

01:20:50.166 --> 01:20:51.916
And you looked badass.

01:20:52.041 --> 01:20:53.625
Yeah, I did.

01:20:55.458 --> 01:20:57.791
[uplifting music]

01:20:57.916 --> 01:21:00.583
We did it, little guy.

01:21:00.708 --> 01:21:01.666
Up high.

01:21:11.583 --> 01:21:13.125
[♪ Jeff Cardoni:
“Best Friends”]

01:21:13.250 --> 01:21:16.833
♪ How to keep your love away? ♪

01:21:21.416 --> 01:21:22.583
Best friends, Bri?

01:21:24.375 --> 01:21:26.208
Best friends, Bri-Bri.

01:21:34.708 --> 01:21:36.250
How are we gonna get home?

01:21:38.166 --> 01:21:41.083
We don't have a car.

01:21:41.208 --> 01:21:43.416
I guess we'll just have
to steal another one, huh?

01:21:43.541 --> 01:21:45.583
Attaboy, Bri.

01:21:45.708 --> 01:21:47.000
Hey, one second.

01:21:47.125 --> 01:21:48.083
What are we gonna do
with all those

01:21:48.208 --> 01:21:49.833
psycho killing machines
in there?

01:21:49.958 --> 01:21:50.916
[remote whirs]

01:21:51.041 --> 01:21:52.250
Kaboom, bitch!

01:21:54.500 --> 01:21:57.041
[♪ The Dead Drums:
"Tune in For the Revolution"]

01:21:58.375 --> 01:22:00.666
♪ Let's go! ♪

01:22:00.791 --> 01:22:03.791
♪ Ah-hah, yeah ♪

01:22:03.916 --> 01:22:06.541
♪ Come on, ha-ha ♪

01:22:06.666 --> 01:22:08.666
♪ Yeah ♪

01:22:08.791 --> 01:22:11.041
♪ Got my picture on the wall
like a VIP ♪

01:22:11.166 --> 01:22:13.583
♪ next to the no-check sign
that's just me ♪

01:22:13.708 --> 01:22:16.750
♪ Tell me, what a loser ♪

01:22:21.875 --> 01:22:24.458
♪ Tune in for the revolution ♪

01:22:30.833 --> 01:22:34.250
[rap music]

01:22:35.375 --> 01:22:36.291
[clears throat] Hey.

01:22:36.416 --> 01:22:37.791
-Butthead.
-[balloon squeaks]

01:22:37.916 --> 01:22:39.125
I've been meaning to ask you.

01:22:39.250 --> 01:22:41.250
I'm so sorry.

01:22:41.375 --> 01:22:42.291
You know what they say?

01:22:42.416 --> 01:22:44.416
-[balloon squeaks]
-Sorry.

01:22:45.500 --> 01:22:46.708
[laughter]

01:22:46.833 --> 01:22:48.291
I'm not back in town, Bri!

01:22:49.583 --> 01:22:51.625
He's a very dangerous
12-year-old.

01:22:51.750 --> 01:22:52.833
-[director] All right.
-Yeah.

01:22:52.958 --> 01:22:54.208
-[tires screech]
-[car crashes]

01:22:54.333 --> 01:22:56.041
Not a good idea, Bri-Bri.

01:22:56.166 --> 01:22:58.041
Hey, what's up?

01:23:00.791 --> 01:23:02.916
[laughter]

01:23:03.041 --> 01:23:04.083
[ice rattles]

01:23:04.208 --> 01:23:05.291
What?

